const jp = .21;
function LE(t) {
    return t * (1 + jp)
}
function Ct(t, s=!0) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return "0,00 €";
    let r;
    return typeof t == "string" ? r = parseFloat(t.replace(",", ".")) : r = t, isNaN(r) || r < 0 ? "0,00 €" : (s && (r = LE(r)), new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
        style: "currency",
        currency: "EUR",
        minimumFractionDigits: 2
    }).format(r))
}
function hL(t) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return {
            basePrice: "0,00 €",
            iva: "0,00 €",
            totalPrice: "0,00 €",
            basePriceNum: 0,
            ivaNum: 0,
            totalPriceNum: 0
        };
    let s;
    if (typeof t == "string" ? s = parseFloat(t.replace(",", ".")) : s = t, isNaN(s) || s < 0)
        return {
            basePrice: "0,00 €",
            iva: "0,00 €",
            totalPrice: "0,00 €",
            basePriceNum: 0,
            ivaNum: 0,
            totalPriceNum: 0
        };
    const r = s * jp,
        n = s + r;
    return {
        basePrice: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(s),
        iva: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(r),
        totalPrice: new Intl.NumberFormat("es-ES", {
            style: "currency",
            currency: "EUR",
            minimumFractionDigits: 2
        }).format(n),
        basePriceNum: s,
        ivaNum: r,
        totalPriceNum: n
    }
}
function fL(t) {
    if (t == null || t === "")
        return "N/A";

}
function pL(t) {

var jL = M2[" useId ".trim().toString()] || (() => {}),

const NL = ["top", "right", "bottom", "left"],
    co = Math.min,
    en = Math.max,
    pf = Math.round,
    Xm = Math.floor,
    Na = t => ({
        x: t,
        y: t
    }),
    wL = {
        left: "right",
        right: "left",
        bottom: "top",
        top: "bottom"
    },
    CL = {
        start: "end",
        end: "start"
    };
function Sv(t, s, r) {
    return en(t, co(s, r))
}
function gi(t, s) {
    return typeof t == "function" ? t(s) : t
}
function vi(t) {
    return t.split("-")[0]
}
function Qc(t) {
    return t.split("-")[1]
}
function Dj(t) {
    return t === "x" ? "y" : "x"
}
function Oj(t) {
    return t === "y" ? "height" : "width"
}
function uo(t) {
    return ["top", "bottom"].includes(vi(t)) ? "y" : "x"
}
function Lj(t) {
    return Dj(uo(t))
}
function SL(t, s, r) {
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);
    const n = Qc(t),
        a = Lj(t),
        i = Oj(a);
    let o = a === "x" ? n === (r ? "end" : "start") ? "right" : "left" : n === "start" ? "bottom" : "top";
    return s.reference[i] > s.floating[i] && (o = xf(o)), [o, xf(o)]
}
function EL(t) {
    const s = xf(t);
    return [Ev(t), s, Ev(s)]
}
function Ev(t) {
    return t.replace(/start|end/g, s => CL[s])
}
function kL(t, s, r) {
    const n = ["left", "right"],
        a = ["right", "left"],
        i = ["top", "bottom"],
        o = ["bottom", "top"];
    switch (t) {
    case "top":
    case "bottom":
        return r ? s ? a : n : s ? n : a;
    case "left":
    case "right":
        return s ? i : o;
    default:
        return []
    }
}
function PL(t, s, r, n) {
    const a = Qc(t);
    let i = kL(vi(t), r === "start", n);
    return a && (i = i.map(o => o + "-" + a), s && (i = i.concat(i.map(Ev)))), i
}
function xf(t) {
    return t.replace(/left|right|bottom|top/g, s => wL[s])
}
function _L(t) {
    return {
        top: 0,
        right: 0,
        bottom: 0,
        left: 0,
        ...t
    }
}
function BE(t) {
    return typeof t != "number" ? _L(t) : {
        top: t,
        right: t,
        bottom: t,
        left: t
    }
}
function gf(t) {
    const {x: s, y: r, width: n, height: a} = t;
    return {
        width: n,
        height: a,
        top: r,
        left: s,
        right: s + n,
        bottom: r + a,
        x: s,
        y: r
    }
}
function iw(t, s, r) {
    let {reference: n, floating: a} = t;
    const i = uo(s),
        o = Lj(s),
        l = Oj(o),
        c = vi(s),
        d = i === "y",
        u = n.x + n.width / 2 - a.width / 2,
        m = n.y + n.height / 2 - a.height / 2,
        f = n[l] / 2 - a[l] / 2;
    let y;
    switch (c) {
    case "top":
        y = {
            x: u,
            y: n.y - a.height
        };
        break;
    case "bottom":
        y = {
            x: u,
            y: n.y + n.height
        };
        break;
    case "right":
        y = {
            x: n.x + n.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    case "left":
        y = {
            x: n.x - a.width,
            y: m
        };
        break;
    default:
        y = {
            x: n.x,
            y: n.y
        }
    }
    switch (Qc(s)) {
    case "start":
        y[o] -= f * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break;
    case "end":
        y[o] += f * (r && d ? -1 : 1);
        break
    }
    return y
}
const TL = async (t, s, r) => {

async function vu(t, s) {

        }) : p);

const AL = t => ({

function bp() {
    return typeof window < "u"
}
function Zc(t) {
    return qE(t) ? (t.nodeName || "").toLowerCase() : "#document"
}
function cn(t) {
    var s;
    return (t == null || (s = t.ownerDocument) == null ? void 0 : s.defaultView) || window
}
function Ma(t) {
    var s;
    return (s = (qE(t) ? t.ownerDocument : t.document) || window.document) == null ? void 0 : s.documentElement

function qE(t) {
    return bp() ? t instanceof Node || t instanceof cn(t).Node : !1
}
function Zn(t) {
    return bp() ? t instanceof Element || t instanceof cn(t).Element : !1
}
function ka(t) {
    return bp() ? t instanceof HTMLElement || t instanceof cn(t).HTMLElement : !1
}
function cw(t) {
    return !bp() || typeof ShadowRoot > "u" ? !1 : t instanceof ShadowRoot || t instanceof cn(t).ShadowRoot
}
function am(t) {

    return /auto|scroll|overlay|hidden|clip/.test(s + n + r) && !["inline", "contents"].includes(a)
}
function zL(t) {
    return ["table", "td", "th"].includes(Zc(t))
}
function Np(t) {
    return [":popover-open", ":modal"].some(s => {
        try {
            return t.matches(s)
        } catch {
            return !1
        }
    })
}
function Fj(t) {
    const s = zj(),
        r = Zn(t) ? Xn(t) : t;

}
function $L(t) {

    for (; ka(s) && !Ec(s);) {
        if (Fj(s))
            return s;

    }

}
function zj() {
    return typeof CSS > "u" || !CSS.supports ? !1 : CSS.supports("-webkit-backdrop-filter", "none")

function Xn(t) {

function mo(t) {

        return t;

function HE(t) {

function kv(t) {

function WE(t) {

    }

function $j(t) {
    return Zn(t) ? t : t.contextElement
}
function Xl(t) {

    }

function UL(t, s, r) {

function sl(t, s, r, n) {
    s === void 0 && (s = !1),
    r === void 0 && (r = !1);

        i = $j(t);
    let o = Na(1);
    s && (n ? Zn(n) && (o = Xl(n)) : o = Xl(t));

    let c = (a.left + l.x) / o.x,
        d = (a.top + l.y) / o.y,
        u = a.width / o.x,
        m = a.height / o.y;

            y = n && Zn(n) ? cn(n) : n;

            x = kv(g);

        }
    }

        width: u,
        height: m,

    })

function Vj(t, s) {

function BL(t) {
    let {elements: s, rect: r, offsetParent: n, strategy: a} = t;
    const i = a === "fixed",
        o = Ma(n),
        l = s ? Np(s.floating) : !1;
    if (n === o || l && i)
        return r;

            scrollLeft: 0,
            scrollTop: 0
        },
        d = Na(1);
    const u = Na(0),
        m = ka(n);
    if ((m || !m && !i) && ((Zc(n) !== "body" || am(o)) && (c = wp(n)), ka(n))) {

        d = Xl(n),
        u.x = y.x + n.clientLeft,
        u.y = y.y + n.clientTop
    }

        width: r.width * d.x,

        y: r.y * d.y - c.scrollTop * d.y + u.y + f.y
    }
}
function qL(t) {

}
function HL(t) {

function Qj() {

        a = !0;

        parseInt(n.split(".")[0]) < 70 && s.push("Chrome version is outdated. Some features may not work correctly.")

        r = "Firefox";
        const i = t.match(/Firefox\/(\d+\.\d+)/);

        n = i ? i[1] : "Unknown"
    }
    return {
        name: r,
        version: n,
        isSupported: a,
        warnings: s
    }
}

function QF(t, s) {
    return s !== "rtl" ? t : t === "ArrowLeft" ? "ArrowRight" : t === "ArrowRight" ? "ArrowLeft" : t
}
function ZF(t, s, r) {
    const n = QF(t.key, r);
    if (!(s === "vertical" && ["ArrowLeft", "ArrowRight"].includes(n)) && !(s === "horizontal" && ["ArrowUp", "ArrowDown"].includes(n)))
        return YF[n]
}
function S4(t, s=!1) {
    const r = document.activeElement;
    for (const n of t)
        if (n === r || (n.focus({
            preventScroll: s
        }), document.activeElement !== r))
            return
}
function XF(t, s) {
    return t.map((r, n) => t[(s + n) % t.length])
}

        measureSize: d,
        direction: f
    }
}
function il(t=0, s=0) {
    const r = as(t - s);
    function n(d) {
        return d < t
    }
    function a(d) {
        return d > s
    }
    function i(d) {
        return n(d) || a(d)
    }
    function o(d) {
        return i(d) ? n(d) ? t : s : d
    }
    function l(d) {
        return r ? d - r * Math.ceil((d - s) / r) : d
    }
    return {
        length: r,
        max: s,
        min: t,
        constrain: o,
        reachedAny: i,
        reachedMax: a,
        reachedMin: n,
        removeOffset: l
    }
}
function YP(t, s, r) {
    const {constrain: n} = il(0, t),
        a = t + 1;

        return r ? as((a + f) % a) : n(f)
    }
    function l() {
        return i
    }
    function c(f) {
        return i = o(f), m
    }
    function d(f) {
        return u().set(l() + f)
    }
    function u() {
        return YP(t, l(), r)
    }
    const m = {
        get: l,
        set: c,
        add: d,
        clone: u
    };
    return m
}
function a$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o, l, c, d, u, m, f, y, g, x, b, j, p) {
    const {cross: v, direction: N} = t,
        w = ["INPUT", "SELECT", "TEXTAREA"],
        C = {
            passive: !1
        },
        S = Pu(),
        T = Pu(),
        L = il(50, 225).constrain(y.measure(20)),

            mouse: 300,

        },

        },

        U = 0,
        D = 0,

    function ie(oe) {
        if (!p)
            return;

            ($p(p) || p(oe, ct)) && Pe(ct)
        }

    }
    function Z(oe) {

    }

        return (g ? F : H)[z ? "mouse" : "touch"]
    }

            ct = u.byDistance(oe, !g).distance;

    }

    }

    }

    }

    }

function v$(t, s, r, n, a) {
    const {reachedAny: i, removeOffset: o, constrain: l} = n;

    }
    function d(g) {
        const x = t ? o(g) : l(g),
            b = s.map((p, v) => ({
                diff: u(p - x, 0),
                index: v
            })).sort((p, v) => as(p.diff) - as(v.diff)),
            {index: j} = b[0];
        return {
            index: j,
            distance: x
        }
    }

        const b = [g, g + r, g - r];

            return g;

            return c(b);

        }

            };

            distance: w
        }
    }
    return {
        byDistance: f,
        byIndex: m,
        shortcut: u
    }
}
function y$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o) {

function b$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o, l, c) {

function N$(t, s, r) {

function w$(t, s, r, n) {

        o = null,

        c = !1;

            }), i = null, o = null, r.emit("slidesInView"))
        }, {

            threshold: n
        }),
        s.forEach(g => l.observe(g))
    }
    function u() {
        l && l.disconnect(),
        c = !0
    }

        return ku(a).reduce((x, b) => {

        }, [])
    }

        if (g && i)
            return i;

            return o;

    }

        init: d,
        destroy: u,

    }

function C$(t, s, r, n, a, i) {
    const {measureSize: o, startEdge: l, endEdge: c} = t,
        d = r[0] && a,
        u = g(),
        m = x(),
        f = r.map(o),
        y = b();
    function g() {
        if (!d)
            return 0;
        const p = r[0];
        return as(s[l] - p[l])
    }
    function x() {
        if (!d)
            return 0;
        const p = i.getComputedStyle(Gn(n));
        return parseFloat(p.getPropertyValue(`margin-${c}`))
    }
    function b() {
        return r.map((p, v, N) => {
            const w = !v,
                C = b0(N, v);
            return w ? f[v] + u : C ? f[v] + m : N[v + 1][l] - p[l]
        }).map(as)
    }

        slideSizes: f,
        slideSizesWithGaps: y,

    }

function S$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o, l, c) {
    const {startEdge: d, endEdge: u, direction: m} = t,
        f = y0(r);
    function y(j, p) {
        return Eu(j).filter(v => v % p === 0).map(v => j.slice(v, v + p))
    }
    function g(j) {
        return j.length ? Eu(j).reduce((p, v, N) => {
            const w = Gn(p) || 0,
                C = w === 0,
                S = v === xm(j),
                T = a[d] - i[w][d],
                L = a[d] - i[v][u],
                H = !n && C ? m(o) : 0,
                F = !n && S ? m(l) : 0,
                A = as(L - F - (T + H));
            return N && A > s + c && p.push(v), S && p.push(j.length), p
        }, []).map((p, v, N) => {
            const w = Math.max(N[v - 1] || 0);
            return j.slice(w, p)
        }) : []
    }
    function x(j) {
        return f ? y(j, r) : g(j)
    }
    return {
        groupSlides: x
    }
}
function E$(t, s, r, n, a, i, o) {

function k$() {
    let t = {},
        s;
    function r(d) {
        s = d
    }
    function n(d) {
        return t[d] || []
    }
    function a(d) {
        return n(d).forEach(u => u(s, d)), c
    }
    function i(d, u) {
        return t[d] = n(d).concat([u]), c
    }
    function o(d, u) {
        return t[d] = n(d).filter(m => m !== u), c
    }
    function l() {
        t = {}
    }
    const c = {
        init: r,
        emit: a,
        off: o,
        on: i,
        clear: l
    };
    return c
}

function _$(t) {
    function s(i, o) {
        return KP(i, o || {})
    }
    function r(i) {

            l = ku(o).filter(c => t.matchMedia(c).matches).map(c => o[c]).reduce((c, d) => s(c, d), {});
        return s(i, l)
    }
    function n(i) {
        return i.map(o => ku(o.breakpoints || {})).reduce((o, l) => o.concat(l), []).map(t.matchMedia)
    }
    return {
        mergeOptions: s,
        optionsAtMedia: r,
        optionsMediaQueries: n
    }
}
function T$(t) {

        s = s.filter(i => i.destroy())
    }
    return {

        destroy: n
    }
}
function Pf(t, s, r) {
    const n = t.ownerDocument,
        a = n.defaultView,
        i = _$(a),
        o = T$(i),
        l = Pu(),
        c = k$(),

        {on: f, off: y, emit: g} = c,
        x = F;

        j,
        p = d(P$, Pf.globalOptions),
        v = d(p),
        N = [],
        w,
        C,
        S;
    function T() {
        const {container: me, slides: oe} = v;
        C = (Zv(me) ? t.querySelector(me) : me) || t.children[0];
        const ye = Zv(oe) ? C.querySelectorAll(oe) : oe;

    }
    function L(me) {

                loop: !1
            });

        }

    }
    function H(me, oe) {
        b || (p = d(p, me), v = u(p), N = oe || N, T(), j = L(v), m([p, ...N.map(({options: fe}) => fe)]).forEach(fe => l.add(fe, "change", F)), v.active && (j.translate.to(j.location.get()), j.animation.init(), j.slidesInView.init(), j.slideFocus.init(se), j.eventHandler.init(se), j.resizeHandler.init(se), j.slidesHandler.init(se), j.options.loop && j.slideLooper.loop(), C.offsetParent && S.length && j.dragHandler.init(se), w = o.init(se, N)))

    }

        j.eventStore.clear(),
        j.translate.clear(),
        j.slideLooper.clear(),

        j.slidesHandler.destroy(),

    }

        U(oe, me, 1)
    }
    function E() {

    }
    function R() {
        return j.index.add(-1).get() !== O()
    }
    function z() {

    }

    }
    function O() {

    }
    function M() {

    }
    function Z() {

    }
    function de() {
        return j.slidesInView.get(!1)
    }
    function je() {

    }
    function Pe() {

    }
    function k() {

    }

    }

        slideNodes: G,

    };

}

        async deleteImportFromHistory(t) {
            const s = await fetch(`/api/import/${t}`, {
                method: "DELETE",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!s.ok) {
                const n = await s.json().catch(() => ({
                    message: "Error desconocido"
                }));
                throw new Error(n.message || "Error al eliminar importación del historial")
            }
            const r = await s.text();
            if (!r || r.trim() === "")
                return {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Importación eliminada correctamente"
                };
            try {
                return JSON.parse(r)
            } catch (n) {
                return console.error("Error parsing JSON response:", n, "Response text:", r), {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Importación eliminada correctamente"
                }
            }
        },
        async deleteAllImportHistory() {
            const t = await fetch("/api/import/clear-all", {
                method: "DELETE",
                headers: {
                    "Content-Type": "application/json"
                },
                credentials: "include"
            });
            if (!t.ok) {
                const r = await t.json().catch(() => ({
                    message: "Error desconocido"
                }));
                throw new Error(r.message || "Error al eliminar todo el historial de importaciones")
            }

                    success: !0,
                    message: "Historial eliminado correctamente"
                };
            try {
                return JSON.parse(s)
            } catch (r) {
                return console.error("Error parsing JSON response:", r, "Response text:", s), {
                    success: !0,
                    message: "Historial eliminado correctamente"
                }
            }
        },

                queryKey: ["parts-brands-models"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    var x,
                        b;

                    try {
                        const j = await w0.getBrandsAndModels();
                        return console.log("=== HERO: Resultado recibido ===", {
                            brands: ((x = j == null ? void 0 : j.brands) == null ? void 0 : x.length) || 0,
                            firstBrands: ((b = j == null ? void 0 : j.brands) == null ? void 0 : b.slice(0, 5)) || [],
                            modelsCount: Object.keys((j == null ? void 0 : j.models) || {}).length
                        }), j
                    } catch (j) {
                        throw console.error("=== HERO: Error al cargar marcas ===", j), j
                    }
                },
                staleTime: 10 * 60 * 1e3,
                retry: 3
            }),

            queryKey: ["parts-brands-models", s, n],
            queryFn: () => fetch(`/api/parts/brands-models?marca=${s || "all-brands"}&modelo=${n || "all-models"}`).then(x => x.json()),
            staleTime: 5 * 60 * 1e3
        });
        const {data: y} = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/parts/families", s, n],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    try {
                        const x = new URLSearchParams;
                        s && s !== "all-brands" && x.append("marca", s),
                        n && n !== "all-models" && x.append("modelo", n),
                        console.log("Consultando familias con filtros:", {
                            marca: s,
                            modelo: n
                        });
                        const b = `/api/optimized/parts/families?${x.toString()}`,
                            j = await fetch(b);
                        if (!j.ok)
                            throw new Error(`Error ${j.status}: ${j.statusText}`);
                        const p = await j.json();
                        if (Array.isArray(p) && p.length > 0 && typeof p[0] == "object" && p[0].name)
                            return p.map(C => C.name).sort();
                        if (Array.isArray(p) && p.length > 0 && typeof p[0] == "string")
                            return p.sort();
                        console.log("Fallback a API original de piezas para familias");
                        const v = new URLSearchParams;
                        v.append("limit", "2000"),
                        v.append("activo", "true"),
                        s && s !== "all-brands" && v.append("marca", s),
                        n && n !== "all-models" && v.append("modelo", n);
                        const w = await (await fetch(`/api/parts?${v.toString()}`)).json();
                        return Array.from(new Set(w.data.map(C => C.descripcionFamilia).filter(Boolean))).sort()
                    } catch (x) {
                        return console.error("Error al cargar familias:", x), []
                    }
                },
                staleTime: 3e4
            }),
            g = x => {
                x.preventDefault();
                const b = new URLSearchParams;
                l.trim() && b.append("search", l.trim()),
                s && s !== "all-brands" && s !== "" && b.append("marca", s),
                n && n !== "all-models" && n !== "" && b.append("modelo", n),
                i && i !== "all-families" && i !== "" && b.append("familia", i),

                    search: l,
                    marca: s,
                    modelo: n,

                }),

            };

function Mr(t, s, r="name") {
    let n = document.querySelector(`meta[${r}="${t}"]`);
    n || (n = document.createElement("meta"), n.setAttribute(r, t), document.head.appendChild(n)),
    n.setAttribute("content", s)
}

    r || (r = document.createElement("script"), r.id = t, r.type = "application/ld+json", document.head.appendChild(r)),
    r.textContent = JSON.stringify(s)
}

            };

                const K = window.innerWidth < 1024;

                    width: window.innerWidth,

                }),

            };

        }, []);

                L(m)
            }, 500);

        }, [m]),

            s && B.set("marca", s),

                    B.append("withPartCounts", "true"),
                    B.append("getTotalCount", "true"),

                        throw new Error(`Error: ${K.statusText}`);
                    const qe = await K.json();
                    return {
                        data: qe.data || [],
                        pagination: {
                            total: ((Qe = qe.pagination) == null ? void 0 : Qe.total) || 0,
                            hasMore: (x - 1) * j + j < (((Nt = qe.pagination) == null ? void 0 : Nt.total) || 0)
                        }

var _V = t => {
    const {control: s, checked: r, bubbles: n=!0, defaultChecked: a, ...i} = t,
        o = h.useRef(null),
        l = Rp(r),
        c = Cp(s);
    h.useEffect(() => {
        const u = o.current,
            m = window.HTMLInputElement.prototype,
            y = Object.getOwnPropertyDescriptor(m, "checked").set;
        if (l !== r && y) {
            const g = new Event("click", {
                bubbles: n
            });
            u.indeterminate = no(r),
            y.call(u, no(r) ? !1 : r),
            u.dispatchEvent(g)
        }
    }, [l, r, n]);
    const d = h.useRef(no(r) ? !1 : r);
    return e.jsx("input", {
        type: "checkbox",
        "aria-hidden": !0,
        defaultChecked: a ?? d.current,
        ...i,
        tabIndex: -1,
        ref: o,
        style: {
            ...t.style,
            ...c,
            position: "absolute",
            pointerEvents: "none",
            opacity: 0,
            margin: 0
        }
    })
};
function no(t) {
    return t === "indeterminate"
}
function z_(t) {
    return no(t) ? "indeterminate" : t ? "checked" : "unchecked"
}

function e1(t) {
    if (t.vehicles && t.vehicles.length > 0) {
        const s = t.vehicles[0];
        return {
            id: s.id,
            marca: s.marca,
            modelo: s.modelo,
            version: s.version || "",
            anyo: s.anyo,
            combustible: s.combustible,
            hasValidId: !!s.id
        }
    }
    return t.vehicleId || t.vehicleMarca || t.vehicleModelo ? {
        id: t.vehicleId,
        marca: t.vehicleMarca || "",
        modelo: t.vehicleModelo || "",
        version: t.vehicleVersion || "",
        anyo: t.vehicleAnyo,
        hasValidId: !!t.vehicleId
    } : t.idVehiculo && (t.vehicleMarca || t.vehicleModelo) ? {
        id: void 0,
        marca: t.vehicleMarca || "",
        modelo: t.vehicleModelo || "",
        version: t.vehicleVersion || "",
        anyo: t.vehicleAnyo,
        hasValidId: !1
    } : {
        id: void 0,
        marca: t.marcaVehiculo || "",
        modelo: t.modeloVehiculo || "",
        version: t.versionVehiculo || "",
        anyo: t.anyoVehiculo,
        hasValidId: !1
    }
}
function AV(t, s={}) {
    const {includeYear: r=!1, uppercase: n=!1, includeId: a=!1} = s,
        i = [t.marca, t.modelo, t.version].filter(Boolean);
    r && t.anyo && i.push(`(${t.anyo})`),
    a && t.id && i.push(`ID: ${t.id}`);
    let o = i.join(" ");
    return n ? o.toUpperCase() : o
}
function t1(t, s={}) {
    const {hideLinks: r=!1, contextVehicleId: n, includeYear: a=!1, uppercase: i=!1, showId: o=!1} = s,
        l = AV(t, {
            includeYear: a,
            uppercase: i
        }),
        c = !r && t.hasValidId && t.id !== n;
    return {
        vehicleText: l,
        shouldShowLink: c,
        vehicleId: t.id,
        linkTo: t.id ? `/vehiculos/${t.id}` : void 0,
        displayText: o && t.id ? `${l} (ID: ${t.id})` : l
    }
}

const Fe = Pt.arrayToEnum(["string", "nan", "number", "integer", "float", "boolean", "date", "bigint", "symbol", "function", "undefined", "null", "array", "object", "unknown", "promise", "void", "never", "map", "set"]),
    Ga = t => {
        switch (typeof t) {
        case "undefined":
            return Fe.undefined;

            return Fe.boolean;
        case "function":
            return Fe.function;

class mn extends Error {
    get errors()
    {
        return this.issues
    }
    constructor(s)
    {
        super(),
        this.issues = [],
        this.addIssue = n => {
            this.issues = [...this.issues, n]
        },
        this.addIssues = (n=[]) => {
            this.issues = [...this.issues, ...n]
        };
        const r = new.target.prototype;
        Object.setPrototypeOf ? Object.setPrototypeOf(this, r) : this.__proto__ = r,
        this.name = "ZodError",
        this.issues = s
    }
    format(s)
    {
        const r = s || function(i) {
                return i.message
            },
            n = {
                _errors: []
            },
            a = i => {
                for (const o of i.issues)
                    if (o.code === "invalid_union")
                        o.unionErrors.map(a);
                    else if (o.code === "invalid_return_type")
                        a(o.returnTypeError);
                    else if (o.code === "invalid_arguments")
                        a(o.argumentsError);
                    else if (o.path.length === 0)
                        n._errors.push(r(o));
                    else {
                        let l = n,
                            c = 0;
                        for (; c < o.path.length;) {
                            const d = o.path[c];
                            c === o.path.length - 1 ? (l[d] = l[d] || {
                                _errors: []
                            }, l[d]._errors.push(r(o))) : l[d] = l[d] || {
                                _errors: []
                            },
                            l = l[d],
                            c++
                        }
                    }
            };
        return a(this), n
    }
    static assert(s)
    {
        if (!(s instanceof mn))
            throw new Error(`Not a ZodError: ${s}`)
    }
    toString()
    {
        return this.message
    }
    get message()
    {
        return JSON.stringify(this.issues, Pt.jsonStringifyReplacer, 2)
    }
    get isEmpty()
    {
        return this.issues.length === 0
    }
    flatten(s=r => r.message)
    {
        const r = {},
            n = [];
        for (const a of this.issues)
            a.path.length > 0 ? (r[a.path[0]] = r[a.path[0]] || [], r[a.path[0]].push(s(a))) : n.push(s(a));
        return {
            formErrors: n,
            fieldErrors: r
        }
    }
    get formErrors()
    {
        return this.flatten()
    }
}
mn.create = t => new mn(t);
const Dc = (t, s) => {
    let r;
    switch (t.code) {
    case Ne.invalid_type:
        t.received === Fe.undefined ? r = "Required" : r = `Expected ${t.expected}, received ${t.received}`;
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_literal:
        r = `Invalid literal value, expected ${JSON.stringify(t.expected, Pt.jsonStringifyReplacer)}`;
        break;
    case Ne.unrecognized_keys:
        r = `Unrecognized key(s) in object: ${Pt.joinValues(t.keys, ", ")}`;
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_union:
        r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_union_discriminator:
        r = `Invalid discriminator value. Expected ${Pt.joinValues(t.options)}`;
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_enum_value:
        r = `Invalid enum value. Expected ${Pt.joinValues(t.options)}, received '${t.received}'`;
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_arguments:
        r = "Invalid function arguments";
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_return_type:
        r = "Invalid function return type";
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_date:
        r = "Invalid date";
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_string:
        typeof t.validation == "object" ? "includes" in t.validation ? (r = `Invalid input: must include "${t.validation.includes}"`, typeof t.validation.position == "number" && (r = `${r} at one or more positions greater than or equal to ${t.validation.position}`)) : "startsWith" in t.validation ? r = `Invalid input: must start with "${t.validation.startsWith}"` : "endsWith" in t.validation ? r = `Invalid input: must end with "${t.validation.endsWith}"` : Pt.assertNever(t.validation) : t.validation !== "regex" ? r = `Invalid ${t.validation}` : r = "Invalid";
        break;
    case Ne.too_small:
        t.type === "array" ? r = `Array must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at least" : "more than"} ${t.minimum} element(s)` : t.type === "string" ? r = `String must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at least" : "over"} ${t.minimum} character(s)` : t.type === "number" ? r = `Number must be ${t.exact ? "exactly equal to " : t.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${t.minimum}` : t.type === "date" ? r = `Date must be ${t.exact ? "exactly equal to " : t.inclusive ? "greater than or equal to " : "greater than "}${new Date(Number(t.minimum))}` : r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Ne.too_big:
        t.type === "array" ? r = `Array must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at most" : "less than"} ${t.maximum} element(s)` : t.type === "string" ? r = `String must contain ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "at most" : "under"} ${t.maximum} character(s)` : t.type === "number" ? r = `Number must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "less than or equal to" : "less than"} ${t.maximum}` : t.type === "bigint" ? r = `BigInt must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "less than or equal to" : "less than"} ${t.maximum}` : t.type === "date" ? r = `Date must be ${t.exact ? "exactly" : t.inclusive ? "smaller than or equal to" : "smaller than"} ${new Date(Number(t.maximum))}` : r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Ne.custom:
        r = "Invalid input";
        break;
    case Ne.invalid_intersection_types:
        r = "Intersection results could not be merged";
        break;
    case Ne.not_multiple_of:
        r = `Number must be a multiple of ${t.multipleOf}`;
        break;
    case Ne.not_finite:
        r = "Number must be finite";
        break;
    default:
        r = s.defaultError,
        Pt.assertNever(t)
    }
    return {
        message: r
    }

function U9(t, s) {
    const r = (t.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length,
        n = (s.toString().split(".")[1] || "").length,
        a = r > n ? r : n,
        i = parseInt(t.toFixed(a).replace(".", "")),
        o = parseInt(s.toFixed(a).replace(".", ""));
    return i % o / Math.pow(10, a)
}
class ho extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte,
        this.step = this.multipleOf
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = Number(s.data)), this._getType(s) !== Fe.number) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.number,
                received: i.parsedType
            }), lt
        }
        let n;
        const a = new hr;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "int" ? Pt.isInteger(s.data) || (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: "integer",
                received: "float",
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "min" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data < i.value : s.data <= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.too_small,
                minimum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data > i.value : s.data >= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.too_big,
                maximum: i.value,
                type: "number",
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                exact: !1,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "multipleOf" ? U9(s.data, i.value) !== 0 && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: i.value,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "finite" ? Number.isFinite(s.data) || (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.not_finite,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : Pt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: a.value,
            value: s.data
        }
    }
    gte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !0, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    gt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !1, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    lte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !0, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    lt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !1, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    setLimit(s, r, n, a)
    {
        return new ho({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: s,
                value: r,
                inclusive: n,
                message: Ye.toString(a)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new ho({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    int(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "int",
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    positive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    negative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: 0,
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: s,
            message: Ye.toString(r)
        })
    }
    finite(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "finite",
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    safe(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MIN_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            inclusive: !0,
            value: Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    get minValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get maxValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get isInt()
    {
        return !!this._def.checks.find(s => s.kind === "int" || s.kind === "multipleOf" && Pt.isInteger(s.value))
    }
    get isFinite()
    {
        let s = null,
            r = null;
        for (const n of this._def.checks) {
            if (n.kind === "finite" || n.kind === "int" || n.kind === "multipleOf")
                return !0;
            n.kind === "min" ? (r === null || n.value > r) && (r = n.value) : n.kind === "max" && (s === null || n.value < s) && (s = n.value)
        }
        return Number.isFinite(r) && Number.isFinite(s)
    }
}

class fo extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.min = this.gte,
        this.max = this.lte
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce)
            try {
                s.data = BigInt(s.data)
            } catch {
                return this._getInvalidInput(s)
            }
        if (this._getType(s) !== Fe.bigint)
            return this._getInvalidInput(s);
        let n;
        const a = new hr;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "min" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data < i.value : s.data <= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.too_small,
                type: "bigint",
                minimum: i.value,
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? (i.inclusive ? s.data > i.value : s.data >= i.value) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.too_big,
                type: "bigint",
                maximum: i.value,
                inclusive: i.inclusive,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : i.kind === "multipleOf" ? s.data % i.value !== BigInt(0) && (n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, n), Re(n, {
                code: Ne.not_multiple_of,
                multipleOf: i.value,
                message: i.message
            }), a.dirty()) : Pt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: a.value,
            value: s.data
        }
    }
    _getInvalidInput(s)
    {
        const r = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
        return Re(r, {
            code: Ne.invalid_type,
            expected: Fe.bigint,
            received: r.parsedType
        }), lt
    }
    gte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !0, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    gt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("min", s, !1, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    lte(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !0, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    lt(s, r)
    {
        return this.setLimit("max", s, !1, Ye.toString(r))
    }
    setLimit(s, r, n, a)
    {
        return new fo({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, {
                kind: s,
                value: r,
                inclusive: n,
                message: Ye.toString(a)
            }]
        })
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new fo({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    positive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    negative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !1,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonpositive(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    nonnegative(s)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: BigInt(0),
            inclusive: !0,
            message: Ye.toString(s)
        })
    }
    multipleOf(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "multipleOf",
            value: s,
            message: Ye.toString(r)
        })
    }
    get minValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }
    get maxValue()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s
    }

class Ru extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = !!s.data), this._getType(s) !== Fe.boolean) {
            const n = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.boolean,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt
        }
        return kr(s.data)
    }
}

class cl extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._def.coerce && (s.data = new Date(s.data)), this._getType(s) !== Fe.date) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.date,
                received: i.parsedType
            }), lt
        }
        if (isNaN(s.data.getTime())) {
            const i = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(i, {
                code: Ne.invalid_date
            }), lt
        }
        const n = new hr;
        let a;
        for (const i of this._def.checks)
            i.kind === "min" ? s.data.getTime() < i.value && (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                code: Ne.too_small,
                message: i.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                minimum: i.value,
                type: "date"
            }), n.dirty()) : i.kind === "max" ? s.data.getTime() > i.value && (a = this._getOrReturnCtx(s, a), Re(a, {
                code: Ne.too_big,
                message: i.message,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                maximum: i.value,
                type: "date"
            }), n.dirty()) : Pt.assertNever(i);
        return {
            status: n.value,
            value: new Date(s.data.getTime())
        }
    }
    _addCheck(s)
    {
        return new cl({
            ...this._def,
            checks: [...this._def.checks, s]
        })
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "min",
            value: s.getTime(),
            message: Ye.toString(r)
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return this._addCheck({
            kind: "max",
            value: s.getTime(),
            message: Ye.toString(r)
        })
    }
    get minDate()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "min" && (s === null || r.value > s) && (s = r.value);
        return s != null ? new Date(s) : null
    }
    get maxDate()
    {
        let s = null;
        for (const r of this._def.checks)
            r.kind === "max" && (s === null || r.value < s) && (s = r.value);
        return s != null ? new Date(s) : null
    }
}
cl.create = t => new cl({
    checks: [],
    coerce: (t == null ? void 0 : t.coerce) || !1,
    typeName: it.ZodDate,
    ...pt(t)
});
class Ff extends jt {

            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.symbol,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt
        }
        return kr(s.data)
    }

class Kn extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r, status: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = this._def;
        if (r.parsedType !== Fe.array)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.array,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), lt;
        if (a.exactLength !== null) {
            const o = r.data.length > a.exactLength.value,
                l = r.data.length < a.exactLength.value;
            (o || l) && (Re(r, {
                code: o ? Ne.too_big : Ne.too_small,
                minimum: l ? a.exactLength.value : void 0,
                maximum: o ? a.exactLength.value : void 0,
                type: "array",
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !0,
                message: a.exactLength.message
            }), n.dirty())
        }
        if (a.minLength !== null && r.data.length < a.minLength.value && (Re(r, {
            code: Ne.too_small,
            minimum: a.minLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.minLength.message
        }), n.dirty()), a.maxLength !== null && r.data.length > a.maxLength.value && (Re(r, {
            code: Ne.too_big,
            maximum: a.maxLength.value,
            type: "array",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.maxLength.message
        }), n.dirty()), r.common.async)
            return Promise.all([...r.data].map((o, l) => a.type._parseAsync(new _a(r, o, r.path, l)))).then(o => hr.mergeArray(n, o));
        const i = [...r.data].map((o, l) => a.type._parseSync(new _a(r, o, r.path, l)));
        return hr.mergeArray(n, i)
    }
    get element()
    {
        return this._def.type
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return new Kn({
            ...this._def,
            minLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ye.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return new Kn({
            ...this._def,
            maxLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ye.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    length(s, r)
    {
        return new Kn({
            ...this._def,
            exactLength: {
                value: s,
                message: Ye.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    nonempty(s)
    {
        return this.min(1, s)
    }
}
Kn.create = (t, s) => new Kn({
    type: t,
    minLength: null,
    maxLength: null,
    exactLength: null,
    typeName: it.ZodArray,
    ...pt(s)
});
function Tl(t) {
    if (t instanceof rs) {
        const s = {};
        for (const r in t.shape) {
            const n = t.shape[r];
            s[r] = Ca.create(Tl(n))
        }
        return new rs({
            ...t._def,
            shape: () => s
        })
    } else
        return t instanceof Kn ? new Kn({
            ...t._def,
            type: Tl(t.element)
        }) : t instanceof Ca ? Ca.create(Tl(t.unwrap())) : t instanceof xo ? xo.create(Tl(t.unwrap())) : t instanceof Ta ? Ta.create(t.items.map(s => Tl(s))) : t
}
class rs extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this._cached = null,
        this.nonstrict = this.passthrough,
        this.augment = this.extend
    }
    _getCached()
    {
        if (this._cached !== null)
            return this._cached;
        const s = this._def.shape(),
            r = Pt.objectKeys(s);
        return this._cached = {
            shape: s,
            keys: r
        }
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (this._getType(s) !== Fe.object) {
            const d = this._getOrReturnCtx(s);
            return Re(d, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.object,
                received: d.parsedType
            }), lt
        }
        const {status: n, ctx: a} = this._processInputParams(s),
            {shape: i, keys: o} = this._getCached(),
            l = [];
        if (!(this._def.catchall instanceof ji && this._def.unknownKeys === "strip"))
            for (const d in a.data)
                o.includes(d) || l.push(d);
        const c = [];
        for (const d of o) {
            const u = i[d],
                m = a.data[d];
            c.push({
                key: {
                    status: "valid",
                    value: d
                },
                value: u._parse(new _a(a, m, a.path, d)),
                alwaysSet: d in a.data
            })
        }
        if (this._def.catchall instanceof ji) {
            const d = this._def.unknownKeys;
            if (d === "passthrough")
                for (const u of l)
                    c.push({
                        key: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: u
                        },
                        value: {
                            status: "valid",
                            value: a.data[u]
                        }
                    });
            else if (d === "strict")
                l.length > 0 && (Re(a, {
                    code: Ne.unrecognized_keys,
                    keys: l
                }), n.dirty());
            else if (d !== "strip")
                throw new Error("Internal ZodObject error: invalid unknownKeys value.")
        } else {
            const d = this._def.catchall;
            for (const u of l) {
                const m = a.data[u];
                c.push({
                    key: {
                        status: "valid",
                        value: u
                    },
                    value: d._parse(new _a(a, m, a.path, u)),
                    alwaysSet: u in a.data
                })
            }
        }
        return a.common.async ? Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
            const d = [];
            for (const u of c) {
                const m = await u.key,
                    f = await u.value;
                d.push({
                    key: m,
                    value: f,
                    alwaysSet: u.alwaysSet
                })
            }
            return d
        }).then(d => hr.mergeObjectSync(n, d)) : hr.mergeObjectSync(n, c)
    }
    get shape()
    {
        return this._def.shape()
    }
    strict(s)
    {
        return Ye.errToObj, new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strict",
            ...s !== void 0 ? {
                errorMap: (r, n) => {
                    var a,
                        i,
                        o,
                        l;
                    const c = (o = (i = (a = this._def).errorMap) === null || i === void 0 ? void 0 : i.call(a, r, n).message) !== null && o !== void 0 ? o : n.defaultError;
                    return r.code === "unrecognized_keys" ? {
                        message: (l = Ye.errToObj(s).message) !== null && l !== void 0 ? l : c
                    } : {
                        message: c
                    }
                }
            } : {}
        })
    }
    strip()
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "strip"
        })
    }
    passthrough()
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            unknownKeys: "passthrough"
        })
    }
    extend(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...s
            })
        })
    }
    merge(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            unknownKeys: s._def.unknownKeys,
            catchall: s._def.catchall,
            shape: () => ({
                ...this._def.shape(),
                ...s._def.shape()
            }),
            typeName: it.ZodObject
        })
    }
    setKey(s, r)
    {
        return this.augment({
            [s]: r
        })
    }
    catchall(s)
    {
        return new rs({
            ...this._def,
            catchall: s
        })
    }
    pick(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return Pt.objectKeys(s).forEach(n => {
            s[n] && this.shape[n] && (r[n] = this.shape[n])
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    omit(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return Pt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            s[n] || (r[n] = this.shape[n])
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    deepPartial()
    {
        return Tl(this)
    }
    partial(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return Pt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            const a = this.shape[n];
            s && !s[n] ? r[n] = a : r[n] = a.optional()
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    required(s)
    {
        const r = {};
        return Pt.objectKeys(this.shape).forEach(n => {
            if (s && !s[n])
                r[n] = this.shape[n];
            else {
                let i = this.shape[n];
                for (; i instanceof Ca;)
                    i = i._def.innerType;
                r[n] = i
            }
        }), new rs({
            ...this._def,
            shape: () => r
        })
    }
    keyof()
    {
        return ST(Pt.objectKeys(this.shape))
    }
}
rs.create = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: () => t,
    unknownKeys: "strip",
    catchall: ji.create(),
    typeName: it.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
rs.strictCreate = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: () => t,
    unknownKeys: "strict",
    catchall: ji.create(),
    typeName: it.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
rs.lazycreate = (t, s) => new rs({
    shape: t,
    unknownKeys: "strip",
    catchall: ji.create(),
    typeName: it.ZodObject,
    ...pt(s)
});
class Ou extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s),
            n = this._def.options;
        function a(i) {
            for (const l of i)
                if (l.result.status === "valid")
                    return l.result;
            for (const l of i)
                if (l.result.status === "dirty")
                    return r.common.issues.push(...l.ctx.common.issues), l.result;
            const o = i.map(l => new mn(l.ctx.common.issues));
            return Re(r, {
                code: Ne.invalid_union,
                unionErrors: o
            }), lt
        }
        if (r.common.async)
            return Promise.all(n.map(async i => {
                const o = {
                    ...r,
                    common: {
                        ...r.common,
                        issues: []
                    },
                    parent: null
                };
                return {
                    result: await i._parseAsync({
                        data: r.data,
                        path: r.path,
                        parent: o
                    }),
                    ctx: o
                }
            })).then(a);
        {
            let i;
            const o = [];
            for (const c of n) {
                const d = {
                        ...r,
                        common: {
                            ...r.common,
                            issues: []
                        },
                        parent: null
                    },
                    u = c._parseSync({
                        data: r.data,
                        path: r.path,
                        parent: d
                    });
                if (u.status === "valid")
                    return u;
                u.status === "dirty" && !i && (i = {
                    result: u,
                    ctx: d
                }),
                d.common.issues.length && o.push(d.common.issues)
            }
            if (i)
                return r.common.issues.push(...i.ctx.common.issues), i.result;
            const l = o.map(c => new mn(c));
            return Re(r, {
                code: Ne.invalid_union,
                unionErrors: l
            }), lt
        }
    }
    get options()
    {
        return this._def.options
    }
}
Ou.create = (t, s) => new Ou({
    options: t,
    typeName: it.ZodUnion,
    ...pt(s)
});
const Ba = t => t instanceof zu ? Ba(t.schema) : t instanceof Jn ? Ba(t.innerType()) : t instanceof $u ? [t.value] : t instanceof po ? t.options : t instanceof Vu ? Pt.objectValues(t.enum) : t instanceof Uu ? Ba(t._def.innerType) : t instanceof Iu ? [void 0] : t instanceof Du ? [null] : t instanceof Ca ? [void 0, ...Ba(t.unwrap())] : t instanceof xo ? [null, ...Ba(t.unwrap())] : t instanceof $0 || t instanceof qu ? Ba(t.unwrap()) : t instanceof Bu ? Ba(t._def.innerType) : [];
class Qp extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (r.parsedType !== Fe.object)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.object,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), lt;
        const n = this.discriminator,
            a = r.data[n],
            i = this.optionsMap.get(a);
        return i ? r.common.async ? i._parseAsync({
            data: r.data,
            path: r.path,
            parent: r
        }) : i._parseSync({
            data: r.data,
            path: r.path,
            parent: r
        }) : (Re(r, {
            code: Ne.invalid_union_discriminator,
            options: Array.from(this.optionsMap.keys()),
            path: [n]
        }), lt)
    }
    get discriminator()
    {
        return this._def.discriminator
    }
    get options()
    {
        return this._def.options
    }
    get optionsMap()
    {
        return this._def.optionsMap
    }
    static create(s, r, n)
    {
        const a = new Map;
        for (const i of r) {
            const o = Ba(i.shape[s]);
            if (!o.length)
                throw new Error(`A discriminator value for key \`${s}\` could not be extracted from all schema options`);
            for (const l of o) {
                if (a.has(l))
                    throw new Error(`Discriminator property ${String(s)} has duplicate value ${String(l)}`);
                a.set(l, i)
            }
        }
        return new Qp({
            typeName: it.ZodDiscriminatedUnion,
            discriminator: s,
            options: r,
            optionsMap: a,
            ...pt(n)
        })
    }
}
function dy(t, s) {
    const r = Ga(t),
        n = Ga(s);
    if (t === s)
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: t
        };
    if (r === Fe.object && n === Fe.object) {
        const a = Pt.objectKeys(s),
            i = Pt.objectKeys(t).filter(l => a.indexOf(l) !== -1),
            o = {
                ...t,
                ...s
            };
        for (const l of i) {
            const c = dy(t[l], s[l]);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            o[l] = c.data
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: o
        }
    } else if (r === Fe.array && n === Fe.array) {
        if (t.length !== s.length)
            return {
                valid: !1
            };
        const a = [];
        for (let i = 0; i < t.length; i++) {
            const o = t[i],
                l = s[i],
                c = dy(o, l);
            if (!c.valid)
                return {
                    valid: !1
                };
            a.push(c.data)
        }
        return {
            valid: !0,
            data: a
        }
    } else
        return r === Fe.date && n === Fe.date && +t == +s ? {
            valid: !0,
            data: t
        } : {
            valid: !1
        }
}
class Lu extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = (i, o) => {
                if (ly(i) || ly(o))
                    return lt;
                const l = dy(i.value, o.value);
                return l.valid ? ((cy(i) || cy(o)) && r.dirty(), {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.data
                }) : (Re(n, {
                    code: Ne.invalid_intersection_types
                }), lt)
            };
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all([this._def.left._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }), this._def.right._parseAsync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        })]).then(([i, o]) => a(i, o)) : a(this._def.left._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }), this._def.right._parseSync({
            data: n.data,
            path: n.path,
            parent: n
        }))
    }
}
Lu.create = (t, s, r) => new Lu({
    left: t,
    right: s,
    typeName: it.ZodIntersection,
    ...pt(r)
});
class Ta extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Fe.array)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.array,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt;
        if (n.data.length < this._def.items.length)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.too_small,
                minimum: this._def.items.length,
                inclusive: !0,
                exact: !1,
                type: "array"
            }), lt;
        !this._def.rest && n.data.length > this._def.items.length && (Re(n, {
            code: Ne.too_big,
            maximum: this._def.items.length,
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            type: "array"
        }), r.dirty());
        const i = [...n.data].map((o, l) => {
            const c = this._def.items[l] || this._def.rest;
            return c ? c._parse(new _a(n, o, n.path, l)) : null
        }).filter(o => !!o);
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all(i).then(o => hr.mergeArray(r, o)) : hr.mergeArray(r, i)
    }
    get items()
    {
        return this._def.items
    }
    rest(s)
    {
        return new Ta({
            ...this._def,
            rest: s
        })
    }
}
Ta.create = (t, s) => {
    if (!Array.isArray(t))
        throw new Error("You must pass an array of schemas to z.tuple([ ... ])");
    return new Ta({
        items: t,
        typeName: it.ZodTuple,
        rest: null,
        ...pt(s)
    })
};
class Fu extends jt {
    get keySchema()
    {
        return this._def.keyType
    }
    get valueSchema()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Fe.object)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.object,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt;
        const a = [],
            i = this._def.keyType,
            o = this._def.valueType;
        for (const l in n.data)
            a.push({
                key: i._parse(new _a(n, l, n.path, l)),
                value: o._parse(new _a(n, n.data[l], n.path, l)),
                alwaysSet: l in n.data
            });
        return n.common.async ? hr.mergeObjectAsync(r, a) : hr.mergeObjectSync(r, a)
    }
    get element()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    static create(s, r, n)
    {
        return r instanceof jt ? new Fu({
            keyType: s,
            valueType: r,
            typeName: it.ZodRecord,
            ...pt(n)
        }) : new Fu({
            keyType: Bn.create(),
            valueType: s,
            typeName: it.ZodRecord,
            ...pt(r)
        })
    }
}
class $f extends jt {
    get keySchema()
    {
        return this._def.keyType
    }
    get valueSchema()
    {
        return this._def.valueType
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Fe.map)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.map,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt;
        const a = this._def.keyType,
            i = this._def.valueType,
            o = [...n.data.entries()].map(([l, c], d) => ({
                key: a._parse(new _a(n, l, n.path, [d, "key"])),
                value: i._parse(new _a(n, c, n.path, [d, "value"]))
            }));
        if (n.common.async) {
            const l = new Map;
            return Promise.resolve().then(async () => {
                for (const c of o) {
                    const d = await c.key,
                        u = await c.value;
                    if (d.status === "aborted" || u.status === "aborted")
                        return lt;
                    (d.status === "dirty" || u.status === "dirty") && r.dirty(),
                    l.set(d.value, u.value)
                }
                return {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                }
            })
        } else {
            const l = new Map;
            for (const c of o) {
                const d = c.key,
                    u = c.value;
                if (d.status === "aborted" || u.status === "aborted")
                    return lt;
                (d.status === "dirty" || u.status === "dirty") && r.dirty(),
                l.set(d.value, u.value)
            }
            return {
                status: r.value,
                value: l
            }
        }
    }

class dl extends jt {
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (n.parsedType !== Fe.set)
            return Re(n, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.set,
                received: n.parsedType
            }), lt;
        const a = this._def;
        a.minSize !== null && n.data.size < a.minSize.value && (Re(n, {
            code: Ne.too_small,
            minimum: a.minSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.minSize.message
        }), r.dirty()),
        a.maxSize !== null && n.data.size > a.maxSize.value && (Re(n, {
            code: Ne.too_big,
            maximum: a.maxSize.value,
            type: "set",
            inclusive: !0,
            exact: !1,
            message: a.maxSize.message
        }), r.dirty());
        const i = this._def.valueType;
        function o(c) {
            const d = new Set;
            for (const u of c) {
                if (u.status === "aborted")
                    return lt;
                u.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(),
                d.add(u.value)
            }
            return {
                status: r.value,
                value: d
            }
        }
        const l = [...n.data.values()].map((c, d) => i._parse(new _a(n, c, n.path, d)));
        return n.common.async ? Promise.all(l).then(c => o(c)) : o(l)
    }
    min(s, r)
    {
        return new dl({
            ...this._def,
            minSize: {
                value: s,
                message: Ye.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    max(s, r)
    {
        return new dl({
            ...this._def,
            maxSize: {
                value: s,
                message: Ye.toString(r)
            }
        })
    }
    size(s, r)
    {
        return this.min(s, r).max(s, r)
    }
    nonempty(s)
    {
        return this.min(1, s)
    }
}

    maxSize: null,
    typeName: it.ZodSet,
    ...pt(s)

class tc extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        this.validate = this.implement
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {ctx: r} = this._processInputParams(s);
        if (r.parsedType !== Fe.function)
            return Re(r, {
                code: Ne.invalid_type,
                expected: Fe.function,
                received: r.parsedType
            }), lt;
        function n(l, c) {
            return Of({
                data: l,
                path: r.path,
                errorMaps: [r.common.contextualErrorMap, r.schemaErrorMap, Df(), Dc].filter(d => !!d),
                issueData: {
                    code: Ne.invalid_arguments,
                    argumentsError: c
                }
            })
        }
        function a(l, c) {
            return Of({
                data: l,
                path: r.path,
                errorMaps: [r.common.contextualErrorMap, r.schemaErrorMap, Df(), Dc].filter(d => !!d),
                issueData: {
                    code: Ne.invalid_return_type,
                    returnTypeError: c
                }
            })
        }
        const i = {
                errorMap: r.common.contextualErrorMap
            },
            o = r.data;
        if (this._def.returns instanceof Lc) {
            const l = this;
            return kr(async function(...c) {
                const d = new mn([]),
                    u = await l._def.args.parseAsync(c, i).catch(y => {
                        throw d.addIssue(n(c, y)), d
                    }),
                    m = await Reflect.apply(o, this, u);
                return await l._def.returns._def.type.parseAsync(m, i).catch(y => {
                    throw d.addIssue(a(m, y)), d
                })
            })
        } else {
            const l = this;
            return kr(function(...c) {
                const d = l._def.args.safeParse(c, i);
                if (!d.success)
                    throw new mn([n(c, d.error)]);
                const u = Reflect.apply(o, this, d.data),
                    m = l._def.returns.safeParse(u, i);
                if (!m.success)
                    throw new mn([a(u, m.error)]);
                return m.data
            })
        }
    }
    parameters()
    {
        return this._def.args
    }
    returnType()
    {
        return this._def.returns
    }
    args(...s)
    {
        return new tc({
            ...this._def,
            args: Ta.create(s).rest(Ko.create())
        })
    }
    returns(s)
    {
        return new tc({
            ...this._def,
            returns: s
        })
    }
    implement(s)
    {
        return this.parse(s)
    }
    strictImplement(s)
    {
        return this.parse(s)
    }
    static create(s, r, n)
    {
        return new tc({
            args: s || Ta.create([]).rest(Ko.create()),
            returns: r || Ko.create(),
            typeName: it.ZodFunction,
            ...pt(n)
        })
    }
}

class po extends jt {
    constructor()
    {
        super(...arguments),
        Id.set(this, void 0)
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        if (typeof s.data != "string") {
            const r = this._getOrReturnCtx(s),
                n = this._def.values;
            return Re(r, {
                expected: Pt.joinValues(n),
                received: r.parsedType,
                code: Ne.invalid_type
            }), lt
        }
        if (Lf(this, Id) || bT(this, Id, new Set(this._def.values)), !Lf(this, Id).has(s.data)) {
            const r = this._getOrReturnCtx(s),
                n = this._def.values;
            return Re(r, {
                received: r.data,
                code: Ne.invalid_enum_value,
                options: n
            }), lt
        }
        return kr(s.data)
    }
    get options()
    {
        return this._def.values
    }
    get enum()
    {
        const s = {};
        for (const r of this._def.values)
            s[r] = r;
        return s
    }
    get Values()
    {
        const s = {};
        for (const r of this._def.values)
            s[r] = r;
        return s
    }
    get Enum()
    {
        const s = {};
        for (const r of this._def.values)
            s[r] = r;
        return s
    }
    extract(s, r=this._def)
    {
        return po.create(s, {
            ...this._def,
            ...r
        })
    }
    exclude(s, r=this._def)
    {
        return po.create(this.options.filter(n => !s.includes(n)), {
            ...this._def,
            ...r
        })
    }
}

class Lc extends jt {

    }

class Jn extends jt {
    innerType()
    {
        return this._def.schema
    }
    sourceType()
    {
        return this._def.schema._def.typeName === it.ZodEffects ? this._def.schema.sourceType() : this._def.schema
    }
    _parse(s)
    {
        const {status: r, ctx: n} = this._processInputParams(s),
            a = this._def.effect || null,
            i = {
                addIssue: o => {
                    Re(n, o),
                    o.fatal ? r.abort() : r.dirty()
                },
                get path() {
                    return n.path
                }
            };
        if (i.addIssue = i.addIssue.bind(i), a.type === "preprocess") {
            const o = a.transform(n.data, i);
            if (n.common.async)
                return Promise.resolve(o).then(async l => {
                    if (r.value === "aborted")
                        return lt;
                    const c = await this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                        data: l,
                        path: n.path,
                        parent: n
                    });
                    return c.status === "aborted" ? lt : c.status === "dirty" || r.value === "dirty" ? Bl(c.value) : c
                });
            {
                if (r.value === "aborted")
                    return lt;
                const l = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: o,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                return l.status === "aborted" ? lt : l.status === "dirty" || r.value === "dirty" ? Bl(l.value) : l
            }
        }
        if (a.type === "refinement") {
            const o = l => {
                const c = a.refinement(l, i);
                if (n.common.async)
                    return Promise.resolve(c);
                if (c instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Async refinement encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return l
            };
            if (n.common.async === !1) {
                const l = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                return l.status === "aborted" ? lt : (l.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(), o(l.value), {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.value
                })
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                }).then(l => l.status === "aborted" ? lt : (l.status === "dirty" && r.dirty(), o(l.value).then(() => ({
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l.value
                }))))
        }
        if (a.type === "transform")
            if (n.common.async === !1) {
                const o = this._def.schema._parseSync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                });
                if (!ll(o))
                    return o;
                const l = a.transform(o.value, i);
                if (l instanceof Promise)
                    throw new Error("Asynchronous transform encountered during synchronous parse operation. Use .parseAsync instead.");
                return {
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                }
            } else
                return this._def.schema._parseAsync({
                    data: n.data,
                    path: n.path,
                    parent: n
                }).then(o => ll(o) ? Promise.resolve(a.transform(o.value, i)).then(l => ({
                    status: r.value,
                    value: l
                })) : o);
        Pt.assertNever(a)
    }
}

    schema: t,
    typeName: it.ZodEffects,
    effect: s,
    ...pt(r)
});

                        code: "custom",

                    })
                }
            });

                d = (o = (i = c.fatal) !== null && i !== void 0 ? i : r) !== null && o !== void 0 ? o : !0;

            })
