function k7({value: t=[], onChange: s, maxImages: r=5, maxSizeBytes: n=5 * 1024 * 1024, acceptedTypes: a=["image/jpeg", "image/jpg", "image/png", "image/webp"], className: i, disabled: o=!1}) {
    const [l, c] = h.useState(!1),
        [d, u] = h.useState(t),
        m = h.useRef(null),
        f = async x => {
            const b = Array.from(x.target.files || []);
            if (b.length !== 0) {
                if (d.length + b.length > r) {
                    alert(`Solo se pueden subir un máximo de ${r} imágenes`);
                    return
                }
                c(!0);
                try {
                    const j = [],
                        p = [];
                    for (const w of b) {
                        if (!a.includes(w.type)) {
                            alert(`Tipo de archivo no válido: ${w.type}. Solo se permiten: ${a.join(", ")}`);
                            continue
                        }
                        if (w.size > n) {
                            alert(`El archivo ${w.name} es demasiado grande. Máximo: ${n / (1024 * 1024)}MB`);
                            continue
                        }
                        const C = URL.createObjectURL(w);
                        p.push(C);
                        const S = new FormData;
                        S.append("image", w);
                        const T = await fetch("/api/upload-image", {
                            method: "POST",
                            body: S
                        });
                        if (T.ok) {
                            const L = await T.json();
                            j.push(L.imageUrl)
                        } else
                            console.error("Error uploading image:", w.name),
                            URL.revokeObjectURL(C)
                    }
                    const v = [...t, ...j],
                        N = [...d, ...p];
                    s(v),
                    u(N)
                } catch (j) {
                    console.error("Error uploading images:", j)
                } finally {
                    c(!1),
                    m.current && (m.current.value = "")
                }
            }
        },
        y = x => {
            const b = t.filter((v, N) => N !== x),
                j = d.filter((v, N) => N !== x),
                p = d[x];
            p && p.startsWith("blob:") && URL.revokeObjectURL(p),
            s(b),
            u(j)
        },
        g = () => {
            var x;
            (x = m.current) == null || x.click()
        };
    return e.jsxs("div", {
        className: ue("space-y-4", i),
        children: [e.jsx($, {
            className: "border-dashed",
            children: e.jsx(V, {
                className: "p-6",
                children: e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "text-center",
                    children: [e.jsx($s, {
                        className: "mx-auto h-12 w-12 text-muted-foreground/50 mb-4"
                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-sm text-muted-foreground mb-4",
                        children: ["Subir imágenes del vehículo (", d.length, "/", r, ")"]
                    }), e.jsx("input", {
                        ref: m,
                        type: "file",
                        multiple: !0,
                        accept: a.join(","),
                        onChange: f,
                        className: "hidden",
                        disabled: o || l || d.length >= r
                    }), e.jsxs(_, {
                        type: "button",
                        variant: "outline",
                        onClick: g,
                        disabled: o || l || d.length >= r,
                        className: "w-full",
                        children: [e.jsx(li, {
                            className: "h-4 w-4 mr-2"
                        }), l ? "Subiendo..." : "Seleccionar imágenes"]
                    }), e.jsxs("p", {
                        className: "text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2",
                        children: ["Máximo ", r, " imágenes, ", n / (1024 * 1024), "MB por imagen"]
                    })]
                })
            })
        }), d.length > 0 && e.jsx("div", {
            className: "grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4",
            children: d.map((x, b) => e.jsx("div", {
                className: "relative group",
                children: e.jsx($, {
                    children: e.jsx(V, {
                        className: "p-2",
                        children: e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "relative aspect-square",
                            children: [e.jsx("img", {
                                src: x,
                                alt: `Imagen ${b + 1}`,
                                className: "w-full h-full object-cover rounded"
                            }), e.jsx(_, {
                                type: "button",
                                variant: "destructive",
                                size: "sm",
                                className: "absolute top-1 right-1 h-6 w-6 p-0 opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity",

                                disabled: o || l,
                                children: e.jsx(er, {
                                    className: "h-3 w-3"
                                })
                            })]
                        })
                    })
                })
            }, b))
        })]
    })
}

            case 2:
                return r + "nd";
            case 3:
                return r + "rd"
            }
        return r + "th"
    },
    yU = {
        ordinalNumber: vU,
        era: pa({
            values: mU,
            defaultWidth: "wide"
        }),
        quarter: pa({
            values: hU,
            defaultWidth: "wide",
            argumentCallback: t => t - 1
        }),
        month: pa({
            values: fU,
            defaultWidth: "wide"
        }),
        day: pa({
            values: pU,
            defaultWidth: "wide"
        }),
        dayPeriod: pa({
            values: xU,
            defaultWidth: "wide",
            formattingValues: gU,
            defaultFormattingWidth: "wide"
        })
    };
function xa(t) {
    return (s, r={}) => {
        const n = r.width,
            a = n && t.matchPatterns[n] || t.matchPatterns[t.defaultMatchWidth],
            i = s.match(a);
        if (!i)
            return null;
        const o = i[0],
            l = n && t.parsePatterns[n] || t.parsePatterns[t.defaultParseWidth],
            c = Array.isArray(l) ? bU(l, m => m.test(o)) : jU(l, m => m.test(o));
        let d;
        d = t.valueCallback ? t.valueCallback(c) : c,
        d = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(d) : d;
        const u = s.slice(o.length);
        return {
            value: d,
            rest: u
        }
    }
}
function jU(t, s) {
    for (const r in t)
        if (Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(t, r) && s(t[r]))
            return r
}
function bU(t, s) {
    for (let r = 0; r < t.length; r++)
        if (s(t[r]))
            return r
}
function VT(t) {
    return (s, r={}) => {
        const n = s.match(t.matchPattern);
        if (!n)
            return null;
        const a = n[0],
            i = s.match(t.parsePattern);
        if (!i)
            return null;
        let o = t.valueCallback ? t.valueCallback(i[0]) : i[0];
        o = r.valueCallback ? r.valueCallback(o) : o;
        const l = s.slice(a.length);
        return {
            value: o,
            rest: l
        }
    }
}
const NU = /^(\d+)(th|st|nd|rd)?/i,
    wU = /\d+/i,
    CU = {
        narrow: /^(b|a)/i,
        abbreviated: /^(b\.?\s?c\.?|b\.?\s?c\.?\s?e\.?|a\.?\s?d\.?|c\.?\s?e\.?)/i,
        wide: /^(before christ|before common era|anno domini|common era)/i
    },
    SU = {
        any: [/^b/i, /^(a|c)/i]
    },
    EU = {
        narrow: /^[1234]/i,
        abbreviated: /^q[1234]/i,
        wide: /^[1234](th|st|nd|rd)? quarter/i
    },
    kU = {
        any: [/1/i, /2/i, /3/i, /4/i]
    },
    PU = {
        narrow: /^[jfmasond]/i,
        abbreviated: /^(jan|feb|mar|apr|may|jun|jul|aug|sep|oct|nov|dec)/i,
        wide: /^(january|february|march|april|may|june|july|august|september|october|november|december)/i
    },
    _U = {
        narrow: [/^j/i, /^f/i, /^m/i, /^a/i, /^m/i, /^j/i, /^j/i, /^a/i, /^s/i, /^o/i, /^n/i, /^d/i],
        any: [/^ja/i, /^f/i, /^mar/i, /^ap/i, /^may/i, /^jun/i, /^jul/i, /^au/i, /^s/i, /^o/i, /^n/i, /^d/i]
    },
    TU = {
        narrow: /^[smtwf]/i,
        short: /^(su|mo|tu|we|th|fr|sa)/i,
        abbreviated: /^(sun|mon|tue|wed|thu|fri|sat)/i,
        wide: /^(sunday|monday|tuesday|wednesday|thursday|friday|saturday)/i
    },
    AU = {
        narrow: [/^s/i, /^m/i, /^t/i, /^w/i, /^t/i, /^f/i, /^s/i],
        any: [/^su/i, /^m/i, /^tu/i, /^w/i, /^th/i, /^f/i, /^sa/i]
    },
    MU = {
        narrow: /^(a|p|mi|n|(in the|at) (morning|afternoon|evening|night))/i,
        any: /^([ap]\.?\s?m\.?|midnight|noon|(in the|at) (morning|afternoon|evening|night))/i
    },
    RU = {
        any: {
            am: /^a/i,
            pm: /^p/i,
            midnight: /^mi/i,
            noon: /^no/i,
            morning: /morning/i,
            afternoon: /afternoon/i,
            evening: /evening/i,
            night: /night/i
        }
    },
    IU = {
        ordinalNumber: VT({
            matchPattern: NU,
            parsePattern: wU,
            valueCallback: t => parseInt(t, 10)
        }),
        era: xa({
            matchPatterns: CU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: SU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        quarter: xa({
            matchPatterns: EU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: kU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any",
            valueCallback: t => t + 1
        }),
        month: xa({
            matchPatterns: PU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: _U,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        day: xa({
            matchPatterns: TU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "wide",
            parsePatterns: AU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        }),
        dayPeriod: xa({
            matchPatterns: MU,
            defaultMatchWidth: "any",
            parsePatterns: RU,
            defaultParseWidth: "any"
        })
    },
    K0 = {
        code: "en-US",
        formatDistance: aU,
        formatLong: cU,
        formatRelative: uU,
        localize: yU,
        match: IU,
        options: {
            weekStartsOn: 0,
            firstWeekContainsDate: 1
        }
    };
function DU(t) {
    const s = ut(t);
    return va(s, zT(s)) + 1
}
function UT(t) {
    const s = ut(t),
        r = +ul(s) - +H7(s);
    return Math.round(r / H0) + 1
}
function BT(t, s) {
    var u,
        m,
        f,
        y;
    const r = ut(t),
        n = r.getFullYear(),
        a = td(),
        i = (s == null ? void 0 : s.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((m = (u = s == null ? void 0 : s.locale) == null ? void 0 : u.options) == null ? void 0 : m.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? a.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((y = (f = a.locale) == null ? void 0 : f.options) == null ? void 0 : y.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        o = Gr(t, 0);
    o.setFullYear(n + 1, 0, i),
    o.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const l = Aa(o, s),
        c = Gr(t, 0);
    c.setFullYear(n, 0, i),
    c.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const d = Aa(c, s);
    return r.getTime() >= l.getTime() ? n + 1 : r.getTime() >= d.getTime() ? n : n - 1
}
function OU(t, s) {
    var l,
        c,
        d,
        u;
    const r = td(),
        n = (s == null ? void 0 : s.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((c = (l = s == null ? void 0 : s.locale) == null ? void 0 : l.options) == null ? void 0 : c.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? r.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((u = (d = r.locale) == null ? void 0 : d.options) == null ? void 0 : u.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        a = BT(t, s),
        i = Gr(t, 0);
    return i.setFullYear(a, 0, n), i.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), Aa(i, s)

function qT(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = +Aa(r, s) - +OU(r, s);
    return Math.round(n / H0) + 1

function Ot(t, s) {
    const r = t < 0 ? "-" : "",
        n = Math.abs(t).toString().padStart(s, "0");
    return r + n
}

function w1(t, s="") {
    const r = t > 0 ? "-" : "+",
        n = Math.abs(t),
        a = Math.trunc(n / 60),
        i = n % 60;
    return i === 0 ? r + String(a) : r + String(a) + s + Ot(i, 2)
}
function C1(t, s) {
    return t % 60 === 0 ? (t > 0 ? "-" : "+") + Ot(Math.abs(t) / 60, 2) : _o(t, s)
}
function _o(t, s="") {
    const r = t > 0 ? "-" : "+",
        n = Math.abs(t),
        a = Ot(Math.trunc(n / 60), 2),
        i = Ot(n % 60, 2);
    return r + a + s + i
}
const S1 = (t, s) => {
        switch (t) {
        case "P":
            return s.date({
                width: "short"
            });
        case "PP":
            return s.date({
                width: "medium"
            });
        case "PPP":
            return s.date({
                width: "long"
            });
        case "PPPP":
        default:
            return s.date({
                width: "full"
            })
        }
    },
    HT = (t, s) => {
        switch (t) {
        case "p":
            return s.time({
                width: "short"
            });
        case "pp":
            return s.time({
                width: "medium"
            });
        case "ppp":
            return s.time({
                width: "long"
            });
        case "pppp":
        default:
            return s.time({
                width: "full"
            })
        }
    },
    LU = (t, s) => {
        const r = t.match(/(P+)(p+)?/) || [],
            n = r[1],
            a = r[2];
        if (!a)
            return S1(t, s);
        let i;
        switch (n) {
        case "P":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "short"
            });
            break;
        case "PP":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "medium"
            });
            break;
        case "PPP":
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "long"
            });
            break;
        case "PPPP":
        default:
            i = s.dateTime({
                width: "full"
            });
            break
        }
        return i.replace("{{date}}", S1(n, s)).replace("{{time}}", HT(a, s))
    },
    FU = {
        p: HT,
        P: LU
    },
    zU = /^D+$/,
    $U = /^Y+$/,
    VU = ["D", "DD", "YY", "YYYY"];
function UU(t) {
    return zU.test(t)
}
function BU(t) {
    return $U.test(t)
}
function qU(t, s, r) {
    const n = HU(t, s, r);
    if (console.warn(n), VU.includes(t))
        throw new RangeError(n)
}
function HU(t, s, r) {
    const n = t[0] === "Y" ? "years" : "days of the month";
    return `Use \`${t.toLowerCase()}\` instead of \`${t}\` (in \`${s}\`) for formatting ${n} to the input \`${r}\`; see: https://github.com/date-fns/date-fns/blob/master/docs/unicodeTokens.md`
}
const WU = /[yYQqMLwIdDecihHKkms]o|(\w)\1*|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g,
    GU = /P+p+|P+|p+|''|'(''|[^'])+('|$)|./g,
    KU = /^'([^]*?)'?$/,
    YU = /''/g,
    QU = /[a-zA-Z]/;
function Kt(t, s, r) {
    var u,
        m,
        f,
        y,
        g,
        x,
        b,
        j;
    const n = td(),
        a = (r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) ?? n.locale ?? K0,
        i = (r == null ? void 0 : r.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? ((m = (u = r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) == null ? void 0 : u.options) == null ? void 0 : m.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? n.firstWeekContainsDate ?? ((y = (f = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : f.options) == null ? void 0 : y.firstWeekContainsDate) ?? 1,
        o = (r == null ? void 0 : r.weekStartsOn) ?? ((x = (g = r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) == null ? void 0 : g.options) == null ? void 0 : x.weekStartsOn) ?? n.weekStartsOn ?? ((j = (b = n.locale) == null ? void 0 : b.options) == null ? void 0 : j.weekStartsOn) ?? 0,
        l = ut(t);
    if (!Q7(l))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    let c = s.match(GU).map(p => {
        const v = p[0];
        if (v === "p" || v === "P") {
            const N = FU[v];
            return N(p, a.formatLong)
        }
        return p
    }).join("").match(WU).map(p => {
        if (p === "''")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: "'"
            };
        const v = p[0];
        if (v === "'")
            return {
                isToken: !1,
                value: ZU(p)
            };
        if (N1[v])
            return {
                isToken: !0,
                value: p
            };
        if (v.match(QU))
            throw new RangeError("Format string contains an unescaped latin alphabet character `" + v + "`");
        return {
            isToken: !1,
            value: p
        }
    });
    a.localize.preprocessor && (c = a.localize.preprocessor(l, c));
    const d = {
        firstWeekContainsDate: i,
        weekStartsOn: o,
        locale: a
    };
    return c.map(p => {
        if (!p.isToken)
            return p.value;
        const v = p.value;
        (!(r != null && r.useAdditionalWeekYearTokens) && BU(v) || !(r != null && r.useAdditionalDayOfYearTokens) && UU(v)) && qU(v, s, String(t));
        const N = N1[v[0]];
        return N(l, v, a.localize, d)
    }).join("")
}
function ZU(t) {
    const s = t.match(KU);
    return s ? s[1].replace(YU, "'") : t
}
function XU(t, s, r) {
    const n = td(),
        a = (r == null ? void 0 : r.locale) ?? n.locale ?? K0,
        i = 2520,
        o = Rh(t, s);
    if (isNaN(o))
        throw new RangeError("Invalid time value");
    const l = Object.assign({}, r, {
        addSuffix: r == null ? void 0 : r.addSuffix,
        comparison: o
    });
    let c,
        d;
    o > 0 ? (c = ut(s), d = ut(t)) : (c = ut(t), d = ut(s));
    const u = rU(d, c),
        m = (zc(d) - zc(c)) / 1e3,
        f = Math.round((u - m) / 60);
    let y;
    if (f < 2)
        return r != null && r.includeSeconds ? u < 5 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 5, l) : u < 10 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 10, l) : u < 20 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXSeconds", 20, l) : u < 40 ? a.formatDistance("halfAMinute", 0, l) : u < 60 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", 1, l) : f === 0 ? a.formatDistance("lessThanXMinutes", 1, l) : a.formatDistance("xMinutes", f, l);
    if (f < 45)
        return a.formatDistance("xMinutes", f, l);
    if (f < 90)
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", 1, l);
    if (f < b1) {
        const g = Math.round(f / 60);
        return a.formatDistance("aboutXHours", g, l)
    } else {
        if (f < i)
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", 1, l);
        if (f < lh) {
            const g = Math.round(f / b1);
            return a.formatDistance("xDays", g, l)
        } else if (f < lh * 2)
            return y = Math.round(f / lh), a.formatDistance("aboutXMonths", y, l)
    }
    if (y = sU(d, c), y < 12) {
        const g = Math.round(f / lh);
        return a.formatDistance("xMonths", g, l)
    } else {
        const g = y % 12,
            x = Math.trunc(y / 12);
        return g < 3 ? a.formatDistance("aboutXYears", x, l) : g < 9 ? a.formatDistance("overXYears", x, l) : a.formatDistance("almostXYears", x + 1, l)
    }
}
function JU(t, s) {
    return XU(t, Y7(t), s)
}
function eB(t) {
    const s = ut(t),
        r = s.getFullYear(),
        n = s.getMonth(),
        a = Gr(t, 0);
    return a.setFullYear(r, n + 1, 0), a.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), a.getDate()
}
function tB(t) {
    return Math.trunc(+ut(t) / 1e3)
}
function sB(t) {
    const s = ut(t),
        r = s.getMonth();
    return s.setFullYear(s.getFullYear(), r + 1, 0), s.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0), s
}
function rB(t, s) {
    return Z7(sB(t), Br(t), s) + 1
}
function my(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = ut(s);
    return r.getTime() > n.getTime()
}
function WT(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = ut(s);
    return +r < +n
}
function Y0(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = ut(s);
    return r.getFullYear() === n.getFullYear() && r.getMonth() === n.getMonth()
}
function nB(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = ut(s);
    return r.getFullYear() === n.getFullYear()
}
function mg(t, s) {
    return br(t, -s)
}
function hg(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t),
        n = r.getFullYear(),
        a = r.getDate(),
        i = Gr(t, 0);
    i.setFullYear(n, s, 15),
    i.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);
    const o = eB(i);
    return r.setMonth(s, Math.min(a, o)), r
}
function E1(t, s) {
    const r = ut(t);
    return isNaN(+r) ? Gr(t, NaN) : (r.setFullYear(s), r)
}

    P1 = t => {
        switch (t.toLowerCase()) {
        case "completed":
            return "bg-green-100 text-green-800 dark:bg-green-900 dark:text-green-100";
        case "failed":
            return "bg-red-100 text-red-800 dark:bg-red-900 dark:text-red-100";
        case "partial":
            return "bg-yellow-100 text-yellow-800 dark:bg-yellow-900 dark:text-yellow-100";
        case "processing":
            return "bg-blue-100 text-blue-800 dark:bg-blue-900 dark:text-blue-100";
        default:
            return "bg-gray-100 text-gray-800 dark:bg-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300"
        }
    },
    _1 = t => {
        switch (t) {
        case "vehicles":
            return "Vehículos";
        case "parts":
            return "Piezas";
        case "all":
            return "Vehículos y Piezas";
        default:
            return t
        }
    },
    T1 = t => {
        switch (t.toLowerCase()) {
        case "completed":
            return "Completado";
        case "failed":
            return "Fallido";
        case "partial":
            return "Parcial";
        case "processing":
        case "in_progress":
            return "En progreso";
        case "paused":
            return "Pausado";
        case "cancelled":
            return "Cancelado";
        default:
            return t
        }
    },
    LB = t => (t.status === "failed" || t.status === "partial" || t.status === "paused") && t.details && (t.details.lastId || t.details.vehicles && t.details.vehicles.lastId || t.details.parts && t.details.parts.lastId),
    FB = t => t.status === "processing" || t.status === "in_progress",
    zB = t => t.status === "processing" || t.status === "in_progress" || t.status === "paused",
    $B = ({history: t, isLoading: s, onDelete: r, onResume: n, onPause: a, onCancel: i, pageSize: o=10, onDeleteAll: l, onPauseAll: c}) => {
        const [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
            [m, f] = h.useState(null),
            [y, g] = h.useState([]),
            [x, b] = h.useState(!1),
            [j, p] = h.useState(null),
            {toast: v} = rt(),
            N = fr(),
            [w, C] = h.useState(1),
            S = (w - 1) * o,
            T = S + o,
            L = t.slice(S, T),
            H = Math.ceil(t.length / o),
            F = async () => {
                if (j !== "delete-all") {
                    p("delete-all");
                    try {
                        const O = t.filter(de => de.status === "in_progress" || de.status === "processing");
                        for (const de of O)
                            try {
                                await ss.cancelImport(de.id)
                            } catch (je) {
                                console.error(`Error al cancelar importación ${de.id}:`, je)
                            }
                        const M = await fetch("/api/import/history", {
                            method: "DELETE",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            },
                            credentials: "include"
                        });
                        if (!M.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al eliminar historial");
                        const Z = await M.json();
                        v({
                            title: "Eliminado correctamente",
                            description: Z.message
                        }),
                        l && l()
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al eliminar todas las importaciones:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error",
                            description: "No se pudo eliminar el historial de importaciones",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            A = async () => {
                if (j !== "pause-all") {
                    p("pause-all");
                    try {
                        const O = await fetch("/api/import/history/pause-all", {
                            method: "POST",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        });
                        if (!O.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al pausar importaciones");
                        const M = await O.json();
                        v({
                            title: "Pausado correctamente",
                            description: M.message
                        }),
                        c && c()
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al pausar todas las importaciones:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error",
                            description: "No se pudieron pausar las importaciones",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            I = O => {
                g(M => M.includes(O) ? M.filter(Z => Z !== O) : [...M, O])
            },
            U = () => {
                y.length === t.length ? g([]) : g(t.map(O => O.id))
            },
            D = async () => {
                p("bulk-delete");
                let O = 0,
                    M = 0;
                for (const Z of y)
                    try {
                        await ss.deleteHistoryItem(Z),
                        r && r(Z),
                        O++
                    } catch (de) {
                        console.error(`Error al eliminar registro ${Z}:`, de),
                        M++
                    }
                v({
                    title: "Eliminación masiva completada",
                    description: `${O} registros eliminados. ${M} errores.`,
                    variant: M > 0 ? "destructive" : "default"
                }),
                g([]),
                b(!1),
                p(null)
            },
            P = O => {
                f(O),
                u(!0)
            },
            E = async () => {
                if (m !== null) {
                    try {
                        await ss.deleteHistoryItem(m),
                        r && r(m),
                        v({
                            title: "Eliminado correctamente",
                            description: "El registro ha sido eliminado del historial"
                        })
                    } catch (O) {
                        console.error("Error al eliminar registro:", O),
                        v({
                            title: "Error al eliminar",
                            description: "No se pudo eliminar el registro. Intente nuevamente.",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })
                    }
                    u(!1),
                    f(null)
                }
            },
            R = async O => {
                p(`resume-${O}`);
                try {
                    const M = await fetch(`/api/import/history/${O}/resume`, {
                            method: "POST",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        }),
                        Z = await M.json();
                    if (M.ok && Z.success)
                        v({
                            title: "Importación reanudada",
                            description: Z.message || "La importación se ha reanudado correctamente"
                        }),
                        await N.invalidateQueries({
                            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                        });
                    else
                        throw new Error(Z.message || "Error al reanudar la importación")
                } catch (M) {
                    console.error("Error reanudando importación:", M),
                    v({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: M instanceof Error ? M.message : "No se pudo reanudar la importación",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            z = async O => {
                p(`pause-${O}`);
                try {
                    const M = await fetch(`/api/import/history/${O}/pause`, {
                            method: "POST",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            }
                        }),
                        Z = await M.json();
                    if (M.ok && Z.success)
                        v({
                            title: "Importación pausada",
                            description: Z.message || "La importación se ha pausado correctamente"
                        }),
                        await N.invalidateQueries({
                            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                        });
                    else
                        throw new Error(Z.message || "Error al pausar la importación")
                } catch (M) {
                    console.error("Error pausando importación:", M),
                    v({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: M instanceof Error ? M.message : "No se pudo pausar la importación",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    p(null)
                }
            },
            ie = async O => {
                if (j !== `cancel-${O}`) {
                    p(`cancel-${O}`);

                        await ss.cancelImport(O),
                        v({
                            title: "Importación cancelada",
                            description: "La importación se ha cancelado correctamente"
                        }),

                            description: "No se pudo cancelar la importación. Intente nuevamente.",
                            variant: "destructive"
                        })

                }

            })]

            className: "text-center py-8 border rounded-md",

                className: "text-muted-foreground",

}

                    i.current || (l = r.triggerRef.current) == null || l.focus()
                }),

                        c = l.button === 0 && l.ctrlKey === !0,

                }, {

                        v;
                    if (x === "all" ? v = "/api/metasync-optimized/import/all" : v = `/api/metasync-optimized/import/${x}`, p = await fetch(v, {
                        method: "POST",

                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },

                            fullImport: b,

                        })
                    }), !p.ok)
                        throw new Error(`Error en la importación: ${p.statusText}`);

    KH = ({schedules: t, onSuccess: s}) => {

            [d, u] = h.useState((o == null ? void 0 : o.active) || !0),
            [m, f] = h.useState((o == null ? void 0 : o.startTime) || "02:00"),
            y = async () => {
                if (o) {
                    a(!0);
                    try {
                        await ss.updateSchedule(o.id, {
                            frequency: l,
                            active: d,
                            startTime: m
                        }),
                        r({
                            title: "Sincronización automática actualizada",
                            description: "La configuración de sincronización ha sido actualizada correctamente"

                        r({
                            title: "Error al actualizar",
                            description: "No se pudo actualizar la configuración de sincronización",

                        })

                        a(!1)
                    }

function YH() {
    const {toast: t} = rt(),
        s = fr(),
        [r, n] = h.useState(!1),
        {data: a, isLoading: i, error: o} = Te({
            queryKey: ["/api/import/history"],
            select: g => g || []
        }),
        l = at({
            mutationFn: async () => (n(!0), await Ie("/api/import/recovery", {
                method: "GET"
            })),
            onSuccess: g => {
                var x;
                t({
                    title: "Importaciones recuperadas",
                    description: g.message || `Se han corregido ${((x = g.recoveredImports) == null ? void 0 : x.length) || 0} importaciones`
                }),
                s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                }),
                n(!1)
            },
            onError: g => {
                console.error("Error al recuperar importaciones:", g),
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudieron recuperar las importaciones",
                    variant: "destructive"
                }),
                n(!1)
            }
        }),
        c = at({
            mutationFn: async g => await Ie(`/api/import/recovery/${g}`, {
                method: "POST"
            }),
            onSuccess: g => {
                t({
                    title: "Importación completada",
                    description: `La importación ${g.importId} ha sido marcada como completada`
                }),
                s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                })
            },
            onError: g => {
                console.error("Error al marcar importación como completada:", g),
                t({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: "No se pudo marcar la importación como completada",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        }),
        d = g => g ? new Date(g).toLocaleString("es-ES") : "N/A",
        u = (g, x) => {
            if (!g)
                return "N/A";
            const b = new Date(g),
                p = (x ? new Date(x) : new Date).getTime() - b.getTime(),
                v = Math.floor(p / 6e4),
                N = Math.floor(v / 60);
            return N > 0 ? `${N}h ${v % 60}m` : `${v}m`
        },
        m = (a == null ? void 0 : a.filter(g => g.status === "running" && new Date(g.startTime).getTime() < Date.now() - 30 * 60 * 1e3)) || [],
        f = () => {
            l.mutate()
        },
        y = g => {
            c.mutate(g)
        };
    return i ? e.jsx("div", {
        className: "flex items-center justify-center p-6",
        children: e.jsx(Xt, {
            className: "h-8 w-8 animate-spin text-primary"
        })
    }) : o ? e.jsxs(lr, {
        variant: "destructive",
        children: [e.jsx(Lr, {
            className: "h-4 w-4"
        }), e.jsx(Ki, {
            children: "Error"
        }), e.jsx(cr, {
            children: "No se pudo cargar el historial de importaciones"
        })]
    }) : e.jsxs($, {
        className: "w-full",
        children: [e.jsxs(ne, {
            children: [e.jsx(ae, {
                children: "Recuperación de Importaciones"
            }), e.jsx(Bt, {
                children: 'Gestiona las importaciones que se han quedado en estado "en progreso"'
            })]
        }), e.jsx(V, {
            children: m.length === 0 ? e.jsxs(lr, {
                children: [e.jsx(Ft, {
                    className: "h-4 w-4"
                }), e.jsx(Ki, {
                    children: "¡Todo en orden!"
                }), e.jsx(cr, {
                    children: "No hay importaciones bloqueadas en este momento."
                })]
            }) : e.jsxs(e.Fragment, {
                children: [e.jsxs(lr, {
                    variant: "warning",
                    className: "mb-4",
                    children: [e.jsx(Lr, {
                        className: "h-4 w-4"
                    }), e.jsx(Ki, {
                        children: "Importaciones bloqueadas"
                    }), e.jsxs(cr, {
                        children: ["Se han detectado ", m.length, ' importaciones que llevan más de 30 minutos en estado "en progreso"']
                    })]
                }), e.jsxs(Us, {
                    children: [e.jsx(D_, {
                        children: 'Importaciones bloqueadas en estado "en progreso"'
                    }), e.jsx(Bs, {
                        children: e.jsxs(yt, {
                            children: [e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "ID"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "Tipo"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "Inicio"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "Duración"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "Estado"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {
                                children: "Acciones"
                            })]
                        })
                    }), e.jsx(qs, {
                        children: m.map(g => e.jsxs(yt, {
                            children: [e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: g.id
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: g.type === "vehicles" ? "Vehículos" : g.type === "parts" ? "Piezas" : g.type === "all" ? "Completa" : g.type
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: d(g.startTime)
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: u(g.startTime, g.endTime)
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: e.jsx(ve, {
                                    variant: "secondary",
                                    className: "bg-yellow-500 hover:bg-yellow-600",
                                    children: "En progreso"
                                })
                            }), e.jsx(pe, {
                                children: e.jsxs(_, {
                                    size: "sm",
                                    onClick: () => y(g.id),
                                    disabled: c.isPending,
                                    children: [c.isPending && c.variables === g.id ? e.jsx(Xt, {
                                        className: "mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin"
                                    }) : null, "Marcar como completada"]
                                })
                            })]
                        }, g.id))
                    })]
                })]
            })
        }), e.jsxs(Pa, {
            className: "flex justify-between",
            children: [e.jsx(_, {
                variant: "outline",
                onClick: () => s.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/import/history"]
                }),
                children: "Actualizar lista"
            }), e.jsxs(_, {
                onClick: f,
                disabled: r || m.length === 0,
                children: [r ? e.jsx(Xt, {
                    className: "mr-2 h-4 w-4 animate-spin"
                }) : null, "Recuperar todas"]
            })]
        })]
    })
}

                    await ss.createSchedule(a),

                    }),

                                            })]

                                            children: [e.jsx("li", {
                                                children: "El API key no tiene permisos suficientes"
                                            }), e.jsx("li", {

                                            })]

                                            }), e.jsx("li", {

                                            })]
                                        })]
                                    })]
                                })]
                            })
                        })]
                    }, y))
                })]
            })]
        }), e.jsx(V, {
            className: "pt-5",
            children: t && e.jsxs("div", {

                    }), "Validación de conteos y recuperación de datos", e.jsx(ve, {

                    })]
                }), e.jsxs(Us, {

                                children: "Métrica"
                            }), e.jsx(ge, {

                            })]
                        })
                    }), e.jsxs(qs, {

                            }), e.jsx(pe, {

                                }) : e.jsx("span", {

                }), t.vehicleCount > 0 && t.vehiclesRetrieved === 0 && e.jsxs("div", {

                    }), " Los conteos muestran vehículos disponibles pero no se pudieron recuperar directamente. Intente recuperar vehículos a través de la API de piezas, donde aparecen como elementos asociados."]
                })]
            })
        }), e.jsxs(Pa, {
            className: "flex gap-2",
            children: [e.jsxs(_, {
                variant: "outline",

                }), "Actualizar diagnóstico"]
            }), e.jsxs(_, {

function Wf(t) {
    return t ? parseInt(t, 10) : 0
}
function HA(t, s) {
    const r = t / s;
    return isNaN(r) ? 0 : r
}
function ex(t) {
    const s = HA(t.viewport, t.content),
        r = t.scrollbar.paddingStart + t.scrollbar.paddingEnd,
        n = (t.scrollbar.size - r) * s;
    return Math.max(n, 18)
}
function dW(t, s, r, n="ltr") {
    const a = ex(r),
        i = a / 2,
        o = s || i,
        l = a - o,
        c = r.scrollbar.paddingStart + o,
        d = r.scrollbar.size - r.scrollbar.paddingEnd - l,
        u = r.content - r.viewport,
        m = n === "ltr" ? [0, u] : [u * -1, 0];
    return WA([c, d], m)(t)
}
function D1(t, s, r="ltr") {
    const n = ex(s),
        a = s.scrollbar.paddingStart + s.scrollbar.paddingEnd,
        i = s.scrollbar.size - a,
        o = s.content - s.viewport,
        l = i - n,
        c = r === "ltr" ? [0, o] : [o * -1, 0],
        d = Jv(t, c);
    return WA([0, o], [0, l])(d)
}
function WA(t, s) {
    return r => {
        if (t[0] === t[1] || s[0] === s[1])
            return s[0];
        const n = (s[1] - s[0]) / (t[1] - t[0]);
        return s[0] + n * (r - t[0])
    }
}
function GA(t, s) {
    return t > 0 && t < s
}
var uW = (t, s=() => {}) => {
    let r = {
            left: t.scrollLeft,
            top: t.scrollTop
        },
        n = 0;
    return function a() {
        const i = {
                left: t.scrollLeft,
                top: t.scrollTop
            },
            o = r.left !== i.left,
            l = r.top !== i.top;
        (o || l) && s(),
        r = i,
        n = window.requestAnimationFrame(a)
    }(), () => window.cancelAnimationFrame(n)
};
function tx(t, s) {
    const r = Zt(t),
        n = h.useRef(0);
    return h.useEffect(() => () => window.clearTimeout(n.current), []), h.useCallback(() => {
        window.clearTimeout(n.current),
        n.current = window.setTimeout(r, s)
    }, [r, s])
}
function Uc(t, s) {
    const r = Zt(s);
    js(() => {
        let n = 0;
        if (t) {
            const a = new ResizeObserver(() => {
                cancelAnimationFrame(n),
                n = window.requestAnimationFrame(r)
            });
            return a.observe(t), () => {
                window.cancelAnimationFrame(n),
                a.unobserve(t)
            }
        }
    }, [t, r])
}

            {data: S, isLoading: T, refetch: L} = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/google-reviews/config"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const E = await (await fetch("/api/google-reviews/config")).json();
                    return E.config || E
                }
            });

            S && !w && (console.log("Loading config into form:", S), o(S.businessName || "Desguace Murcia"), c(S.location || "Murcia, España"), u(S.placeId || ""), f(S.apiKey || ""), g(S.enabled || !1), b(S.minRating || 4), p(S.maxReviews || 6), N(S.cacheHours || 24), C(!0))

                mutationFn: async P => {
                    const E = await fetch("/api/google-reviews/config", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(P)
                    });
                    if (!E.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error saving configuration");

                        title: "✅ Configuración guardada",

                },

                        title: "❌ Error",
                        description: P.message || "No se pudo guardar la configuración.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }

                queryKey: ["/api/google-reviews"],

        var _e,
            Se;

            {toast: s} = rt(),

            [i, o] = h.useState(1),
            [l, c] = h.useState(null),
            [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
            [m, f] = h.useState(!1),
            [y, g] = h.useState("fechaActualizacion"),
            [x, b] = h.useState("desc"),
            [j, p] = h.useState(""),
            [v, N] = h.useState("all"),
            [w, C] = h.useState("all"),
            [S, T] = h.useState({
                min: "",
                max: ""
            }),
            [L, H] = h.useState(!1),
            [F, A] = h.useState(!1),
            [I, U] = h.useState(null),
            [D, P] = h.useState(!1),
            [E, R] = h.useState(null);

        df("/admin/parts/new"),

                queryKey: ["/api/search-parts", i, n, j, v, w, S, y, x],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    try {
                        let ee = `/api/search-parts?limit=${Nd}&offset=${(i - 1) * Nd}&isAdmin=true&getTotalCount=true`;
                        n && (ee += `&q=${encodeURIComponent(n)}`),
                        j && (ee += `&familia=${encodeURIComponent(j)}`),
                        v !== "all" && (ee += `&activo=${v === "active"}`),
                        w !== "all" && (w === "processed" ? ee += "&vehicleType=processed" : w === "associated" && (ee += "&vehicleType=associated")),
                        S.min && (ee += `&precioMin=${S.min}`),
                        S.max && (ee += `&precioMax=${S.max}`),
                        y && (ee += `&orden=${y}_${x}`),
                        console.log("Admin parts query URL:", ee);
                        const Ce = await fetch(ee, {
                            credentials: "include"
                        });
                        if (!Ce.ok)
                            throw new Error("Error al cargar piezas");
                        const Ge = await Ce.json();
                        return console.log("Admin parts response:", Ge), Ge
                    } catch (ee) {
                        throw console.error("Error en la consulta de piezas:", ee), ee
                    }
                },
                enabled: !L && !F
            }),
            {data: M} = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/optimized/parts/families"],
                queryFn: async () => (await fetch("/api/optimized/parts/families")).json()
            }),
            Z = (z == null ? void 0 : z.data) || [],
            de = ((_e = z == null ? void 0 : z.pagination) == null ? void 0 : _e.total) || 0,
            je = ((Se = z == null ? void 0 : z.pagination) == null ? void 0 : Se.filtered) || de,

            k = M || [],
            te = at({
                mutationFn: async ee => {
                    const Ce = await fetch("/api/parts", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        credentials: "include",
                        body: JSON.stringify(ee)
                    });
                    if (!Ce.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al crear pieza");
                    return Ce.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Pieza creada",
                        description: "La pieza ha sido creada correctamente"
                    }),
                    tn.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/search-parts"]
                    }),
                    A(!1),

                },

                    s({
                        title: "Error al crear pieza",
                        description: "No se pudo crear la pieza. Intente nuevamente.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            G = at({
                mutationFn: async ({id: ee, data: Ce}) => {
                    const Ge = await fetch(`/api/parts/${ee}`, {
                        method: "PUT",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        credentials: "include",
                        body: JSON.stringify(Ce)
                    });
                    if (!Ge.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al actualizar pieza");
                    return Ge.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Pieza actualizada",
                        description: "La pieza ha sido actualizada correctamente"
                    }),

                        queryKey: ["/api/search-parts"]
                    }),
                    H(!1),
                    U(null),
                    t("/admin/parts")
                },

                    s({
                        title: "Error al actualizar pieza",
                        description: "No se pudo actualizar la pieza. Intente nuevamente.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),

                mutationFn: async ee => {

                        credentials: "include"

                        throw new Error("Error al eliminar pieza");

            F = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/users"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    try {
                        const M = await fetch("/api/users");
                        if (!M.ok) {
                            const je = await M.json();
                            throw new Error(je.error || "Error al cargar usuarios")
                        }
                        const Z = await M.json();
                        return console.log("Usuarios cargados:", Z), Z.filter(je => je.role === "manager" || je.role === "admin" || je.isAdmin) || []
                    } catch (M) {
                        throw console.error("Error en la consulta de usuarios:", M), M
                    }
                }
            }),
            A = at({
                mutationFn: async M => {
                    const Z = await fetch("/api/users", {
                        method: "POST",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(M)
                    });
                    if (!Z.ok) {
                        const de = await Z.json();
                        throw new Error(de.error || "Error al crear usuario")
                    }
                    return Z.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    s({
                        title: "Usuario creado",
                        description: "El usuario ha sido creado correctamente"
                    }),
                    a(!1),
                    F.refetch(),
                    f(""),
                    g(""),
                    b(""),
                    p("manager")
                },
                onError: M => {
                    s({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: M.message || "Error al crear usuario",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                }
            }),
            I = at({
                mutationFn: async ({id: M, userData: Z}) => {
                    const de = await fetch(`/api/users/${M}`, {
                        method: "PUT",
                        headers: {
                            "Content-Type": "application/json"
                        },
                        body: JSON.stringify(Z)
                    });
                    if (!de.ok) {
                        const je = await de.json();
                        throw new Error(je.error || "Error al actualizar usuario")
                    }
                    return de.json()
                },

                        title: "Usuario actualizado",

                        method: "DELETE"

    kW = () => {
        const [t, s] = h.useState(""),
            [r, n] = h.useState("all"),
            [a, i] = h.useState(""),
            [o, l] = h.useState(null),
            [c, d] = h.useState(null),
            [u, m] = h.useState(!1),
            [f, y] = h.useState(!1),
            [g, x] = h.useState(!1),
            [b, j] = h.useState(null),
            [p, v] = h.useState({}),
            {toast: N} = rt(),
            w = fr(),
            {data: C, isLoading: S} = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const M = await fetch("/api/admin/clients");
                    if (!M.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar clientes");
                    return (await M.json()).filter(de => de.role === "customer" && !de.isAdmin)
                }
            }),
            {data: T, isLoading: L} = Te({
                queryKey: ["/api/admin/guest-orders"],
                queryFn: async () => {
                    const M = await fetch("/api/admin/guest-orders");
                    if (!M.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar pedidos de invitados");
                    return M.json()
                }
            }),
            H = (C == null ? void 0 : C.filter(M => {
                const Z = M.firstName.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || M.lastName.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || M.email.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()) || M.username.toLowerCase().includes(t.toLowerCase()),
                    de = r === "all" || M.province === r;
                return Z && de
            })) || [],
            F = (T == null ? void 0 : T.filter(M => M.guestName.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()) || M.guestEmail.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()) || M.orderNumber.toLowerCase().includes(a.toLowerCase()))) || [],
            A = [...new Set(C == null ? void 0 : C.map(M => M.province).filter(Boolean))],
            I = M => {
                switch (M) {
                case "admin":
                    return "destructive";
                case "manager":
                    return "secondary";
                case "customer":
                    return "default";
                default:
                    return "outline"
                }
            },
            U = M => {
                switch (M) {
                case "admin":
                    return "Administrador";
                case "manager":
                    return "Gestor";
                case "customer":
                    return "Cliente";
                default:
                    return M
                }
            },
            D = at({
                mutationFn: async ({id: M, data: Z}) => {
                    const de = {
                            firstName: Z.firstName,
                            lastName: Z.lastName,
                            email: Z.email,
                            phone: Z.phone,
                            address: Z.address,
                            city: Z.city,
                            postalCode: Z.postalCode,
                            province: Z.province,
                            shippingAddress: Z.shippingAddress,
                            shippingCity: Z.shippingCity,
                            shippingPostalCode: Z.shippingPostalCode,
                            shippingProvince: Z.shippingProvince,
                            billingAddress: Z.billingAddress,
                            billingCity: Z.billingCity,
                            billingPostalCode: Z.billingPostalCode,
                            billingProvince: Z.billingProvince
                        },
                        je = await fetch(`/api/admin/users/${M}`, {
                            method: "PUT",
                            headers: {
                                "Content-Type": "application/json"
                            },
                            body: JSON.stringify(de)
                        });
                    if (!je.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al actualizar cliente");
                    return je.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    w.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"]
                    }),
                    N({
                        title: "Cliente actualizado",
                        description: "Los datos del cliente se han actualizado correctamente"
                    }),
                    y(!1),
                    d(null),
                    v({})
                },
                onError: M => {
                    N({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "No se pudo actualizar el cliente",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    }),
                    console.error("Error updating client:", M)
                }
            }),
            P = at({
                mutationFn: async M => {
                    const Z = await fetch(`/api/admin/users/${M}`, {
                        method: "DELETE"
                    });
                    if (!Z.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al eliminar cliente");
                    return Z.json()
                },
                onSuccess: () => {
                    w.invalidateQueries({
                        queryKey: ["/api/admin/clients"]
                    }),
                    N({
                        title: "Cliente eliminado",
                        description: "El cliente ha sido eliminado correctamente"
                    }),

                        title: "Error",

                        variant: "destructive"
                    }),

                }

            },

            };

                            children: "Cancelar"
                        }), e.jsx(_, {
                            onClick: ie,
                            disabled: D.isPending,
                            children: D.isPending ? "Guardando..." : "Guardar Cambios"
                        })]
                    })]
                })
            }), e.jsx(Oi, {
                open: g,
                onOpenChange: x,
                children: e.jsxs(Ya, {
                    children: [e.jsxs(Qa, {
                        children: [e.jsx(Xa, {
                            children: "¿Eliminar cliente?"
                        }), e.jsxs(Ja, {
                            children: ["Esta acción no se puede deshacer. Se eliminará permanentemente el cliente", b && ` "${b.firstName} ${b.lastName}"`, "y todos sus datos asociados."]
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs(Za, {
                        children: [e.jsx(ti, {
                            children: "Cancelar"
                        }), e.jsx(ei, {
                            onClick: O,
                            className: "bg-red-600 hover:bg-red-700",
                            disabled: P.isPending,
                            children: P.isPending ? "Eliminando..." : "Eliminar"
                        })]
                    })]
                })
            })]
        })
    };
function ii({className: t, ...s}) {
    return e.jsx("div", {
        className: ue("animate-pulse rounded-md bg-muted", t),
        ...s
    })
}
const ya = ({children: t}) => e.jsxs("div", {
    className: "flex min-h-screen bg-gray-100",
    children: [e.jsx(Ls, {}), e.jsxs("div", {
        className: "flex-1 p-8",
        children: [e.jsx("div", {
            className: "mb-6"
        }), e.jsx("div", {
            className: "flex-1",
            children: t
        })]
    })]
});
function PW({order: t, isOpen: s, onClose: r}) {
    const {toast: n} = rt(),
        a = fr(),
        i = h.useRef(null),
        o = h.useRef(null),
        [l, c] = h.useState({
            transportAgency: (t == null ? void 0 : t.transportAgency) || "",
            expeditionNumber: (t == null ? void 0 : t.expeditionNumber) || "",
            adminObservations: (t == null ? void 0 : t.adminObservations) || "",
            documents: (t == null ? void 0 : t.documents) || [],
            invoicePdf: (t == null ? void 0 : t.invoicePdf) || ""
        }),
        [d, u] = h.useState(!1),
        m = at({
            mutationFn: p => (console.log("🚀 Frontend: Enviando actualización de pedido:", {
                orderId: t.id,
                url: `/api/admin/orders/${t.id}/update-admin-info`,
                data: p
            }), Ie("PATCH", `/api/admin/orders/${t.id}/update-admin-info`, p)),
            onSuccess: p => {
                console.log("✅ Frontend: Actualización exitosa:", p),
                n({
                    title: "Pedido actualizado",
                    description: "La información adicional se ha guardado correctamente."
                }),
                a.invalidateQueries({
                    queryKey: ["/api/admin/orders"]
                }),
                r()
            },
            onError: p => {
                var v,
                    N,
                    w,
                    C;
                console.error("❌ Frontend: Error al actualizar pedido:", p),
                console.error("❌ Frontend: Error details:", {
                    message: p.message,
                    response: (v = p.response) == null ? void 0 : v.data,
                    status: (N = p.response) == null ? void 0 : N.status
                }),
                n({
                    title: "Error",
                    description: ((C = (w = p.response) == null ? void 0 : w.data) == null ? void 0 : C.error) || p.message || "No se pudo actualizar el pedido.",
                    variant: "destructive"
                })
            }
        }),
        f = async (p, v) => {
            const N = new FormData;
            N.append("file", p),
            N.append("orderId", t.id.toString()),
            N.append("type", v);
            try {
                const w = await fetch("/api/upload/order-document", {
                    method: "POST",
                    body: N
                });
                if (!w.ok)
                    throw new Error("Error al subir archivo");
                return (await w.json()).filePath
            } catch (w) {
                throw w
            }
        },
        y = async p => {
            const v = p.target.files;
            if (v) {
                u(!0);
                try {
                    const N = Array.from(v).map(C => f(C, "document")),
                        w = await Promise.all(N);
                    c(C => ({
                        ...C,
                        documents: [...C.documents, ...w]
                    })),
                    n({
                        title: "Documentos subidos",
                        description: `Se han subido ${v.length} documento(s) correctamente.`
                    })
                } catch {
                    n({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Error al subir los documentos.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    u(!1),
                    i.current && (i.current.value = "")
                }
            }
        },
        g = async p => {
            var N;
            const v = (N = p.target.files) == null ? void 0 : N[0];
            if (v) {
                if (v.type !== "application/pdf") {
                    n({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Solo se permiten archivos PDF para la factura.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    });
                    return
                }
                u(!0);
                try {
                    const w = await f(v, "invoice");
                    c(C => ({
                        ...C,
                        invoicePdf: w
                    })),
                    n({
                        title: "Factura subida",
                        description: "La factura se ha subido correctamente."
                    })
                } catch {
                    n({
                        title: "Error",
                        description: "Error al subir la factura.",
                        variant: "destructive"
                    })
                } finally {
                    u(!1),
                    o.current && (o.current.value = "")
                }
            }
        },
        x = p => {
            c(v => ({
                ...v,
                documents: v.documents.filter((N, w) => w !== p)
            }))
        },
        b = () => {
            c(p => ({
                ...p,
                invoicePdf: ""
            }))
        },
        j = p => {
            p.preventDefault(),
            m.mutate(l)
        };
    return t ? e.jsx(Cs, {
        open: s,
        onOpenChange: r,
        children: e.jsxs(xs, {
            className: "max-w-2xl max-h-[90vh] overflow-y-auto",
            children: [e.jsx(gs, {
                children: e.jsxs(vs, {
                    children: ["Información Adicional - Pedido ", t.orderNumber]
                })
            }), e.jsxs("form", {
                onSubmit: j,
                className: "space-y-6",
                children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg",
                    children: [e.jsx("h3", {
                        className: "font-semibold mb-2",
                        children: "Información del Pedido"
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        className: "grid grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm",
                        children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Cliente:"
                            }), " ", t.customerName]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Email:"
                            }), " ", t.customerEmail]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Total:"
                            }), " ", t.total, "€"]
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            children: [e.jsx("span", {
                                className: "font-medium",
                                children: "Estado:"
                            }), " ", t.orderStatus]
                        })]
                    })]
                }), e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "space-y-4",
                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: "transportAgency",
                            children: "Agencia de Transporte"
                        }), e.jsx(J, {
                            id: "transportAgency",
                            value: l.transportAgency,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                transportAgency: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Nombre de la agencia de transporte"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: "expeditionNumber",
                            children: "Número de Expedición"
                        }), e.jsx(J, {
                            id: "expeditionNumber",
                            value: l.expeditionNumber,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                expeditionNumber: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Número de seguimiento o expedición"
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            htmlFor: "adminObservations",
                            children: "Observaciones"
                        }), e.jsx(Ut, {
                            id: "adminObservations",
                            value: l.adminObservations,
                            onChange: p => c(v => ({
                                ...v,
                                adminObservations: p.target.value
                            })),
                            placeholder: "Observaciones adicionales para el cliente...",
                            rows: 4
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            children: "Documentos"
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "mt-2",
                            children: [e.jsxs(_, {
                                type: "button",
                                variant: "outline",
                                onClick: () => {
                                    var p;
                                    return (p = i.current) == null ? void 0 : p.click()
                                },
                                disabled: d,
                                className: "mb-3",
                                children: [e.jsx(li, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                                }), d ? "Subiendo..." : "Subir Documentos"]
                            }), e.jsx("input", {
                                ref: i,
                                type: "file",
                                multiple: !0,
                                accept: ".pdf,.jpg,.jpeg,.png",
                                onChange: y,
                                className: "hidden"
                            }), l.documents.length > 0 && e.jsx("div", {
                                className: "space-y-2",
                                children: l.documents.map((p, v) => e.jsxs("div", {
                                    className: "flex items-center justify-between bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded",
                                    children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                        className: "flex items-center",
                                        children: [e.jsx(gu, {
                                            className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                                        }), e.jsx("span", {
                                            className: "text-sm",
                                            children: p.split("/").pop()
                                        })]
                                    }), e.jsx(_, {
                                        type: "button",
                                        variant: "ghost",
                                        size: "sm",
                                        onClick: () => x(v),
                                        children: e.jsx(er, {
                                            className: "w-4 h-4"
                                        })
                                    })]
                                }, v))
                            })]
                        })]
                    }), e.jsxs("div", {
                        children: [e.jsx(q, {
                            children: "Factura PDF"
                        }), e.jsxs("div", {
                            className: "mt-2",
                            children: [e.jsxs(_, {
                                type: "button",
                                variant: "outline",
                                onClick: () => {
                                    var p;
                                    return (p = o.current) == null ? void 0 : p.click()
                                },
                                disabled: d,
                                className: "mb-3",
                                children: [e.jsx(li, {
                                    className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                                }), d ? "Subiendo..." : "Subir Factura PDF"]
                            }), e.jsx("input", {
                                ref: o,
                                type: "file",
                                accept: ".pdf",
                                onChange: g,
                                className: "hidden"
                            }), l.invoicePdf && e.jsxs("div", {
                                className: "flex items-center justify-between bg-gray-50 p-2 rounded",
                                children: [e.jsxs("div", {
                                    className: "flex items-center",
                                    children: [e.jsx(gu, {
                                        className: "w-4 h-4 mr-2"
                                    }), e.jsx("span", {
                                        className: "text-sm",
                                        children: l.invoicePdf.split("/").pop()
                                    })]
                                }), e.jsx(_, {
                                    type: "button",
                                    variant: "ghost",
                                    size: "sm",
                                    onClick: b,
                                    children: e.jsx(er, {
                                        className: "w-4 h-4"
                                    })
                                })]
                            })]
                        })]
                    })]
                }), e.jsxs("div", {
                    className: "flex justify-end space-x-2",
                    children: [e.jsx(_, {
                        type: "button",
                        variant: "outline",
                        onClick: r,
                        children: "Cancelar"
                    }), e.jsx(_, {
                        type: "submit",
                        disabled: m.isPending || d,
                        children: m.isPending ? "Guardando..." : "Guardar Cambios"
                    })]
                })]
            })]
        })
    }) : null
}

            if (t != null && t.id) {
                o(!0);
                try {
                    const u = await fetch(`/api/admin/orders/${t.id}`);
                    if (!u.ok)
                        throw new Error("Error al cargar detalles del pedido");
                    const m = await u.json();
                    a(m)
                } catch (u) {
                    console.error("Error al cargar detalles del pedido:", u)
                } finally {
                    o(!1)
                }
            }
        };
    if (h.useEffect(() => {
        s && l()
    }, [s, t == null ? void 0 : t.id]), !t)
        return null;
    const c = O1[n == null ? void 0 : n.paymentStatus] || O1.pendiente,
        d = L1[n == null ? void 0 : n.orderStatus] || _W[n == null ? void 0 : n.status] || L1.pendiente_verificar;

    })
